title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan to form crust.
Cream the cheese until smooth. Beat eggs slightly with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add pineapple, flour and vanilla.
Blend eggs and cheese mixture.
Pour into crust and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with cherry filling after cooling.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix in order listed in a bowl. Bake in a 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes in 2 round layer cake pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) baking pan.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Cook and stir beef in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, seasoning mix, onion, pepper and mustard. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Spread in ungreased dish and spread topping over the top.

title: rhubarb betty
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Pat half of crumb mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cook next three ingredients until clear.
Add raw rhubarb.
Spread on crumb mixture.
Sprinkle some red jello over rhubarb mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Debone chicken and place in buttered casserole dish; place cooked broccoli over chicken.
Make a sauce of the other ingredients and heat until blended well.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice krispies pie crust
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir well.
Press evenly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Cool.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: monterey jack bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in saucepan and add garlic salt and green chilies.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread butter mixture on bread, then spread cheese and mayo mixture on top of this.
Place on cookie sheet and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Slice into serving pieces.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in large pot on stove.
Add onion, potatoes, soup, water and salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Remove 1 inch skin from stem (to prevent skin from splitting).
Place apples in baking dish.
Fill centers of each apple with 1 tablespoon brown sugar, 1 teaspoon butter and 1/3 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour water 1/4 inch deep in baking dish. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375° until apples are tender when pierced with fork.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and blend well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
For Pyrex pan, use 325° oven.
Grease and flour pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Drain and snap off stems.
Fry and drain sausage.
Fill caps with mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Put under broiler for 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: jello pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Fold milk and jello together with juice of lemon.
Put in vanilla wafer crust and chill.

title: frosty treasures(puppy chow)
directions: First
melt
margarine	or butter in a Dutch oven, then add chocolate morsels and peanut butter, stirring frequently, until melted.
Add
Crispix
cereal
and stir until cereal is completely coated.
Next
in	a large brown paper sack, add 3 cups
of powdered
sugar,
then
add freshly coated cereal to powdered sugar and shake until completely coated.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, then serve as you would candy.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Work flour, sugar and butter together into coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping on cake. Mix together molasses, boiling water and baking soda. Combine with remaining crumbs. Mix well. Batter will be thin. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle the 1 1/2 cups of reserved crumbs over the cake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta with tomatoes, herbs and garlic
directions: In bowl, combine tomatoes, basil, chives, parsley, garlic, oil, cheese, salt and pepper.
Let stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Boil pasta.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Pour sauce over pasta.
Warm before serving.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: festive tropical punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large pot or mixing bowl. Blend fresh fruit pieces together in blender until smooth and pour into juices.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into ice cube trays and freeze or pour into children's popsicle trays.
This makes delicious popsicles for children and freezes solid.
You need quite a few ice cube trays for this.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Start oven at moderate 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking dish. Wash and drain berries.
Look over for discards.
Combine berries with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spread evenly in prepared baking dish.

title: fresh strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar and flour; toss with fruits.
Pour into pastry; dot with butter.
Top and crimp with second crust.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of foil to prevent burning.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until golden or juices begin to bubble through slits you have made in top of crust.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp and layer the shrimp, onions and peppers until gone.
Add bay leaves.
Pour vinegar mixture over layers and refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order thoroughly; pour into pie shell. Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Decorate with pecan halves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend together condensed milk, frozen lemonade and Cool Whip. Add pecans.
Fills 3 pie crusts.
Minute Maid lemonade seems to work best.
(This is good with fresh sliced strawberries blended with nuts.)
Top with blueberry pie mix.
Chill before serving.

title: breakfast for twelve
directions: Place bread in bottom of casserole.
Layer with grated cheese and cooked sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate all night.
In morning, mix mushroom soup with small amount of milk and pour on casserole.
Spread mushrooms over top and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time; mix well.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Pound chicken and wash; dip into egg and milk, then into flour. Saute chicken in butter with garlic.
Remove chicken.
Add to pan water, chicken, bouillon, wine and lemon juice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine or oil until tender; add flour, stirring well.
Add chicken seasoning, then gradually add water. Stir until smooth.
Add broccoli that has been chopped very fine and bay leaf.
Cook over medium heat until tender, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and stir in milk and basil.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef cubes.
Add water and remaining ingredients except cornstarch and sour cream.
Cook 1 hour or until tender.
Mix cornstarch with cold water to make a thin paste.
Thicken stroganoff and remove from heat after 3 minutes.
Add sour cream. Serve over noodles.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole and slice margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and spread on crackers or Hawaiian bread.

title: "buckeye candy"
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter together on low heat.
Add sugar. Mix well.
Roll into balls.
In double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip each ball part way into chocolate.
Hold with a toothpick.
Lay on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 200 pieces.

title: diet pumpkin custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well mixed.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, 45 minutes to 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill; when cool, cut into squares and serve with 1 tablespoon low fat Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer hen until tender in salted water.
When done, cool and cut into chunks, not too fine.
Mix with remainder of ingredients, except mushroom soup, adding eggs last.
Put into baking dish. Pour mushroom soup over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rye bread boat dip
directions: Cut dried beef in small pieces and mix with other 4 ingredients.
Cut top off bread like you would a pumpkin.
Hollow out loaf and cube bread for dipping.
Pour dip in hollow loaf and cover until time to serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Bake in well-greased pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat in microwave.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: bride's cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape in mold overnight.
Remove from mold and roll in chopped pecans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taffie bars
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Add flour and salt. Press into a 9 x 13 inch cake pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: ricotta omelet
directions: Combine chicken or turkey, pineapple and Ricotta cheese.
In nonstick pan, melt butter.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour into pan.
Allow omelet to cook around sides and middle.
Put Ricotta cheese mixture on eggs.
Fold over one side of omelet and continue to cook until eggs are done and not runny.
Sprinkle parsley on top of omelet and serve.

title: picnic salad rolls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, tossing well.
Combine dip, mayonnaise and salt. Mix well and fold into vegetable mixture. Set aside.

title: saltine tailgate dessert
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Lay saltines on cookie sheet.
Boil for 3 minutes butter, brown sugar and sugar. Pour mixture over crackers, then bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Once melted, sprinkle like icing.
Cool, then break up in different shape pieces.

title: cheese-ham pie with dough
directions: Combine the two pieces of dough (the one at the end of the other) and place the slices of ham on top to cover the whole dough.
In a bowl you mix the grated cheese (3 kinds) with the yolks, salt and pepper.
You put the mixture on top of the ham and spread it.
Start folding the dough from the one side.
Make sure the cheese stays inside.
After you fold it place it in a greased cake pan and brush the dough all around with the whites, then you add the sesame and you bake the pie for 30 minutes at 350°.
Good luck.

title: white chocolate ice cream
directions: Saute almonds in butter in skillet over medium heat until crisp, reserve.
Combine cream and milk in saucepan; cook over medium heat until skin forms on surface.
Beat yolks and sugar with vanilla in medium bowl.
Gradually add cream mixture, whisking constantly.
Strain into double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring until mixture thickens and lightly coats back of spoon, about 10 minutes.
Do not boil!
Remove from heat; add Kirsch and white chocolate, stirring until chocolate melts. Cool to room temperature.
Add almonds.
Pour into ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Makes 1 quart.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix well; chill for 2 hours.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Whip the first 3 ingredients until frothy, but not stiff. Stir the nuts (all at one time) into the egg white mix.
In another bowl, mix the sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in nuts and stir until all are completely covered with mixture. Bake on buttered pan for about 1 hour at 250°.
Cool and enjoy. If they stick together, simply break apart.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Place franks in pan.
Combine onion, pepper and celery; cook in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Combine sugar, vinegar and lemon juice.
Add Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard and water.
Add to franks and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: pink cranberry freeze
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend in mayonnaise and sugar. Add fruit and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a loaf pan and freeze at least 6 hours. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving. Remove from pan and slice. Serve on lettuce leaves. Tastes delightful with turkey.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Mix crushed pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 cup melted butter. Spread in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Mix and drop in muffin pan. Cook until done at 325° to 350°.

title: sweet potato slices
directions: Use No. 8 iron skillet. Peel sweet potato and slice. Layer potato slices in hot oil. Add water. Cover and cook on medium heat until tender. Serve on slices of bread. Serves 2.

title: sinatra's italian soup
directions: Fry the pork sausage; drain and place in stockpot. Saute mushrooms, garlic and onion in small amount of olive oil until tender, then add to stockpot. Add tomatoes, chicken broth and seasonings to stockpot and begin to simmer. Cook noodles per directions and then add to stockpot. Simmer slowly until heated through. Soup will taste even better the next day.

title: joyce's casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, meat and cheese until dish is full.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°, then uncover last 10 minutes.
Can also layer margarine every other layer.

title: italian cheese torta
directions: Drop spaghetti into boiling, salted water and boil gently until al dente.
Drain and toss with butter.
Remove sausage from casings and crumble into skillet.
Fry until partially cooked; drain off fat and add onion.
Cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Roast and peel pepper and coarsely chop.
Toss together spaghetti, sausage mixture, olives, eggs, parsley, red pepper, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Turn half into buttered and floured spring-form pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and top with remaining spaghetti mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with Parmesan Cheese Sauce.

title: miriam's middle east carrots
directions: Cook carrots for about 10 minutes.
Let them set in hot water for 5 more minutes.
Carrots should be quite firm but not hard. Drain water.
Mix in all the other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: barbecued hamburg(from 1975 edition)
directions: Fry hamburg, onion, celery and green pepper.
Sprinkle flour over meat.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to meat and vegetables.

title: caribbean corn relish
directions: Combine corn and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil. Simmer 12 minutes (covered). Add everything but cornstarch.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir in cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Put in hot jars.
Seal.
Process 15 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes about 6 1/2 pints.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in basil, paprika and cream cheese.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Use a whisk and mix until soup is smooth and hot.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pressure cooker.
Cook 25 minutes.

title: pasta e fagioli soup
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Add onion and garlic and cook for 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, undrained cannellini beans, chicken broth, parsley, basil and pepper to Dutch oven and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Let boil for approximately 1 minute and then let simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Add pasta to Dutch oven and simmer approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Serve immediately.
Enjoy!

title: corn fritter pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients.
Add water just until batter becomes pourable (a thick batter).
Cook on medium heat in a lightly oiled skillet.
Yum!

title: oat muffins
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a medium sized bowl and mix.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and let stand in refrigerator 1 hour or longer.
Heat oil, 1 to 1 1/2
cups, in pan according to size of pan.
Using ice tea spoon, dip in hot oil and spoon out batter.
Drop into heated oil until brown. They will float and turn over when done.
(Heating spoon each time prevents batter from sticking to spoon.

title: rose tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve over ice.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: broiled herbed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes; discard tops. Arrange tomatoes on rack of a broiler pan coated with cooking spray; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture over cut surface of tomatoes.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Yields 8 servings (57 calories and 30% fat per serving).

title: hawaiian salad(serves 20)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add orange concentrate.
Chill until almost set.
Prepare dessert topping.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water; let this sit until yeast foams, then add enough flour to make like a paste, then let it rise for about 30 minutes at room temperature.
Then you add this to the paste, sugar, eggs, oleo, milk and salt.
Add enough flour to make the dough like for homemade bread.
Let it rise about 1 hour; knead it down, then let it rise again, then they are ready to be put on the tin.
Pull off dough big as an egg for each kolache.
Then make a hole in the center, then put fruit (prunes, apricots, etc.) in center of dough.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours before baking.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Drain tomatoes and cut up.
In a bowl combine the lettuce, cheese, onion, olives and tomatoes.
To the meat add the tomato liquid, bean dip, chili powder and salt. Bring to a boil.
Add to lettuce mix and top with chips.
Serve at once.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 12 ingredients.
Pat into a loaf.
Put in large roaster.
Mix small can of tomato paste, brown sugar, lemon juice and worcestershire sauce together for sauce.
Pour half of sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 300 degrees for 2-3 hours basting with remaining sauce mixture.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet, add margarine.
Cook chicken until brown on both sides.
Remove.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover, cook over low heat for 5 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Stir occasionally.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, paprika, ketchup and onion. Beat well with mixer. Add oil slowly and alternately with vinegar and celery seed.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add salt and pepper. Cook noodles as directed and drain. In a casserole dish, layer sauce, noodles, meat, cottage cheese and shredded cheese. Repeat, making sure shredded cheese is on the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil all together for 10 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm, then add baking soda, baking powder, eggs, vanilla and flour (enough to make a medium stiff batter). Add walnuts if desired.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend together salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Add chopped apples. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy day overnight lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburg; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, add cottage cheese, oregano and egg; mix well.
In bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Top with 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers; top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°; uncover baking dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Fritos and dressing.
Add Fritos and dressing right before serving.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Crumble all of the graham crackers pour in melted butter, mix together. In a separate bowl combine cool whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla flavoring. In a large bowl put a layer of graham crackers. Then put a layer of the cool whip mixture. Then put a layer of cherry pie filling. Start all over with each layer until you use all of the mixes.

title: green bean pork chop bake
directions: Mix together soup and green beans. Add dash of salt.
Place vegetables in casserole dish. Top with browned pork chops. Cover dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange cheese spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl with electric mixer until well blended. Gradually blend into gelatin.
Pour gelatin mixture into mold. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.
Serve as an appetizer with crackers.
Garnish with parsley and carrot curls, if desired. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In microwavable bowl, combine all ingredients.
Put bowl in microwave on High until butter melts, about 1 minute (check often). When butter is melted, mix and stir all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch square pan, lined with wax paper.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: cathie irene's baked beans
directions: In a large saucepan brown bacon and onion. Add remaining ingredients and cook, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes on a low flame. Do not stir too often.
Can be reheated in oven.
Travels well. Freezes well.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: cajun pork roast
directions: Rub surface of loin with oil.
Combine seasonings and rub mixture well over all surfaces of roast.
Place roast in shallow pan and cook in 350° oven for about an hour or until internal temperature is 155°.
Remove from oven and let rest 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat corn tortillas in small amount of grease.
Put spoonfuls of mixture in tortilla and roll up.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and green chillies together and pour over tortillas.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Spread on bottom of greased (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Prepare dressing according to package using chicken broth instead of water.
Spread dressing over broccoli; scatter chicken on top.
Add undiluted soup over chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter and white and brown sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Form into tiny balls and place individual balls in mini cupcake pans. Bake in oven at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven. While still hot,
press mini peanut butter cup (foil removed) in each hot cookie.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy bottomed 2-quart saucepan over high heat, stir sugar, corn syrup and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 300° (hard crack stage), about 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts, margarine, vanilla and baking soda. Quickly spread in thin layer on greased baking sheet; cool.
Break into pieces; store in airtight container for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 16 servings.
Serving size, 1 ounce.

title: mock lobster salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.
You may substitute 1 can tomato soup instead of juice.

title: chocolate cheese cupcakes(for adults only)
directions: Combine and mix dry ingredients.
Combine and mix liquid ingredients.
Mix dry and liquid ingredients together and put in cupcake papers 3/4 full.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in center. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Warm soup, onion, sour cream and peppers.
Warm tortillas slightly for handling ease.
Grease large casserole dish.
Fill tortillas with chicken, soup and mixture and cheese and roll up.
Top with extra soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook in saucepan over low heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell, cover with top crust.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: microwave "cracker jack"
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwave dish.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Shake.
Put bag in microwave and cook for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes. Test popcorn and if too sticky or chewy, cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into a large pan to cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and mix the cream cheese and margarine; stir in sugar. Add eggs.
Add vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in flour; blend mixture well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: preacher's cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large saucepan and boil five minutes.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Drop on wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about three dozen cookies.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine 3/4 cup crumbs, egg, parsley, onion, milk, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salmon and cheese.
Shape into patties. Mix margarine with rest of crumbs.
Coat with mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: festive fudge
directions: In heavy sauce pan over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk and salt. Remove from heat, stir in nuts if desired and vanilla. Spread evenly onto waxed lined 8-9 inch square pan.

title: nachos
directions: Spread beans on each chip.
Top off with fried hamburg.
Cut up vegetables and sprinkle over top.
Pour cheese over all.
Put in oven on broil for about 10 minutes.
Add lettuce.
Serve with sour cream and hot sauce on the side.
I put mine on a large cookie pan.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: Mix the gooseberries and sugar; let set 2 hours.
Mix and let set out 2 cups water and both jellos.
After 2 hours, combine the 2 mixtures, then add the celery, cheese and nuts.
Top with a mixture of Cool Whip and Miracle Whip.

title: quick zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, then stir in zucchini so all is coated. Pour into a buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: e-z chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover.
Remove chicken and cook vegetables in broth.
Mix deboned chicken, vegetables and 1 cup of broth with 2 cans of cream of chicken soup.
In separate pan (casserole dish), layer 1 can of biscuits on the bottom.
Add chicken mixture and top with other can of biscuits.
Cook at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: quick fondue
directions: Mix well
in
saucepan over low heat.
Pour into fondue pot. Place
over
fondue
burner.
Spear with fresh French or sourdough bread squares and dip.

title: ham, potatoes and carrots casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ham in skillet.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of ham, potatoes, carrots and onions until all are used.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Pour on milk mixed with mushroom soup.
If needed, add more milk. Cover.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer, until potatoes are done.

title: easy chicken stew
directions: In saucepan, add water and chicken packets and bring to a boil.
Add carrots, celery and onion and simmer for 5 minutes. Add potatoes, parsley and pepper and cook 5 minutes more.
Then add chicken or turkey and simmer 10 minutes more to blend flavors.

title: bottomless pie (apple)
directions: Place sliced apples in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Mix together soft butter or oleo, brown sugar, flour, spices and egg.
Drop by teaspoon on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil the chicken, broth from the chicken, bouillon cubes, margarine, salt and pepper.
Drop biscuits into boiling juices and cook until biscuits swell to doneness.

title: tuna dip
directions: Fry onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter.
Add tuna, mushroom soup and crab boil.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.

title: pizza pancakes(makes about 14 pancakes)
directions: Heat griddle or skillet; grease if necessary.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with wire whisk until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients (batter will be thick).
Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle; spread slightly.
Cook until edges are dry.
Turn; cook until golden brown.
Serve topped with warm spaghetti sauce.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Beat after each addition. Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes until done. Frost with Lemon Cheese Filling.

title: banana fudge walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of an 8-inch square pan.
Melt in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly the margarine and chocolate chips.
Beat thoroughly with spoon the flour, sugar, chopped walnuts, bananas, vanilla, baking powder, salt and egg.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with vegetables or crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set
oven at 375°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, syrup and
melted
margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into the pie shell. Bake until center is slightly firm.

title: not so sweet pecan pie
directions: Mix and put in one unbaked pie shell.
Bake for about 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and finish baking.

title: shish-kabobs
directions: Marinate sirloin cubes in dressing for at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Cut bell pepper in chunks and onion in quarters and separate.
Thread meat, peppers, onions, and mushrooms on skewers by alternating meat with a vegetable.
Cook on grill until desired doneness.

title: topping for fish
directions: Mix mayonnaise, ketchup, garlic and dry Italian dressing mixture.
Wash fish; dry.
Place on broiling pan.
Coat top of fish with mixture.
Place under broiler until fish is opaque or easily flaked.
Do not turn fish.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve red jello in 2 cups boiling water.

Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Chill until set. Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water. Combine sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan. Heat but do not boil. Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve. Add cream cheese and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Spread over congealed layer.
Chill.
Mix green jello according to package directions and pour over this layer. Chill.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and pecans.
Stir in flour.
Form into small balls, using 1 tablespoon dough for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press balls flat with bottom of a tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until cookies are lightly browned, about 16 to 18 minutes. If desired, sprinkle with red or green sugar crystals, or top with pecan or cherry half.
Makes 42.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Saute hamburg with onion, salt and pepper.
Pour off fat.
Put hamburg in a large pot and cover with water.
Add 1 can whole tomatoes, 1 large can Veg-All (including liquid), 1/2 cup orzo and 3 beef bouillon cubes.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli wellington
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat; drain well.
Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well, simmering 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
On ungreased cookie sheets, overlap long sides of 2 rectangles 1/2 inch. Firmly press edges and perforations to seal.
Press or roll to form 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spoon meat mixture in 3-inch strip lengthwise down center of dough.
Bring long edges of dough rectangle over filling, overlapping edges slightly.
Pinch edge and seal ends.
Repeat with remaining rectangles.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrot slices, water and salt in a medium saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat 15 minutes or just until tender (do not drain).
Combine orange juice, sugar, cornstarch, margarine, and ginger, stirring until well blended.
Pour over carrot slices in saucepan.

title: caramel cashew cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until creamy at medium speed on mixer.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Combine, then add into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls (2 tablespoons dough) on ungreased cookie sheet, about 3-inches apart.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cookies will be moist, but crisp.
Cool about 2 minutes before removing from sheet.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 2 qt. saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt. add milk slowly, stirring constantly until sauce boils and thickens.
Add potatoes.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour into greased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, or until done.
Put cheese on top and let melt.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat all ingredients until blended. Increase speed to medium. Beat until frosting is smooth and creamy, about 2 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake per package directions.
While cake is still warm, poke holes (I use a meat thermometer to make the holes) all over it.
Pour Amaretto into holes and over cake.
Let cool, then cut into 3 sections.

title: sausage wontons
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage.
Prepare Ranch dressing according to package directions.
Mix sausage, cheeses, olives and dressing together in medium bowl.
Press wonton wrappers in miniature muffin tins.
(Grease tins lightly).
Spray wonton wrappers or brush lightly with vegetable oil.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and stuff with filling mixture.
Bake 5 additional minutes until cheese has melted and mixture is bubbly.
Serve warm.
Yield:
36 miniature appetizers.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix bread with ground beef.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano leaves with ground beef and onion. Add tomatoes, that have been put in blender.
Simmer uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Cook lasagne noodles; drain.

title: fried rabbit with brown gravy
directions: Soak rabbit overnight in salted water and vinegar.
Wash in cold water and pat dry; add seasoning.
Coat in flour and place in hot oil.
Fry until brown, remove rabbit from oil.
Sprinkle some flour in oil and let flour brown.
Put rabbit back into skillet with chopped onion.
Add water, stir and simmer on low heat until done.

title: peaches with rum sauce
directions: Put whipped cream, lemon juice, rum and ice cream in a large mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Serve over fresh sliced peaches. Substitute canned fruit for fresh as long as you drain it first.

title: polish cabbage and noodles
directions: Fry cabbage and Polish sausage in oleo in a kettle.
Let simmer 20 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Boil noodles in salted water.
Add drained noodles to cabbage.
Stir to mix well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter and powdered sugar.
(Save 1/2 cup for top.)
Put remainder in the bottom of crust.
Pour prepared pudding over the sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Let set for an hour or so.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar mixture on top.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: sausage delights
directions: Brown hot and mild sausage together in skillet; drain.
Melt cheese.
Mix cheese and browned sausage together.
Spread mixture on slices of bread.
Bake open-faced sandwiches in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 6 tablespoons of cold water.
Add 1 cup hot
water;
let
cool.
Add
pineapple,
lemon
juice and sugar; let thicken.
Use
of
the
Cool
Whip;
mix
with pineapple. Break
angel food cake in small pieces.
Put layer of cake and layer
of
mix into large, round glass dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight, then turn on dish.
Cover with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: yogurt chicken
directions: Mix
ingredients
together in large bowl, then marinate chicken for 2 hours in refrigerator and grill.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave ingredients 3 minutes on High.
Stir 1 minute until chocolate completely melts.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and nuts if desired.
Put into 10 x 10-inch pan lined with wax paper. Refrigerate 2 hours or so.

title: darryl's punch recipe
directions: Mix and serve over crushed ice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, vegetables and stock. Set aside. Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour vegetable and chicken mix into dish. Blend together the Bisquick, milk and margarine until smooth. Pour over chicken and vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: orange mold
directions: Place on bottom of mold a thin layer of sliced peaches or mandarin oranges (canned and drained).
Add a small amount of clear jello to cover and let jell, then add rest of jello mixed with pineapple.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: chili 'n' beans
directions: Melt butter.
Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining items. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick. Serve over hot rice.

title: greek bread
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend mayonnaise and sour cream with butter.
Add olives and chopped onions.
Add cheese. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread on sliced French bread.
Broil until bubbly.

title: hamburger-potato dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in fat in cooker.
Pour off excess fat.
Add potatoes and salt.
Mix soup and water; pour over top. Cover, set control on vent tube and cook 3 minutes after control jiggles.
Reduce pressure instantly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked vegetable macedoine
directions: Place vegetables in an ungreased shallow 2-quart casserole. Gently toss.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender; stir once.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Combine the flour, sugar, butter, butter flavoring and 1/4 to 1/2 cup pecan pieces.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: cornflake cookies(easy for children to do)
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a hard boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until blended and melted.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Seal in a container.

title: uncle jr's berry cobbler
directions: Line pan with pie crust and bread.
Place mixture of berries, sugar, and flour in next on top of the bread.
Put the pats of butter over the berry mixture and cover it all with the remaining pie crust.

title: last minute fruit cake
directions: Place raisins, dates, sugar, shortening and 2 cups of boiling water in saucepan and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool the mixture.
Sift flour, soda and spices together and stir into the cooled mixture. Add nuts last, coated with a little flour.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
When cool, wrap in foil or wax paper.
The cakes stay moist and keep well.

title: cranberry sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Add almond extract.
Alternately add and beat sour cream with flour, baking soda and salt.
Put 1/2 of recipe in buttered tube pan.
Spoon on cranberry sauce.
Put rest of recipe on top. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until tests done.
Either top with a glaze or powdered sugar.

title: breath of spring cake
directions: Measure and beat together first 6 ingredients.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg is added.
Add milk and vanilla. Mixing can be done in one bowl.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: great pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with fork. In a separate bowl, beat next 3 ingredients; then add to first. Stir with fork. Chill 15 minutes. Makes dough for at least 3 pies. Can be kept in the refrigerator or frozen.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: While hot, cut baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides; whip potatoes.
Add butter.
Gradually beat in milk.
Stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon back in shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
If you substitute onion salt, use 2 teaspoons for 3 large potatoes.

title: cockeyed cake icing
directions: Cream the butter.
Add brown sugar; cream and beat until smooth, adding the milk slowly.
Mix in as many nuts or as much coconut, or both, as desired.
Allow the cake to cool just a few minutes in the pan, then spread with the topping.
Bake an additional 5 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Pour into mini cups.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Stir in peanut butter. Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from pan to cooling rack.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together cake mix (remove 1 cup and set aside), melted butter and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together pumpkin, brown sugar, 3 eggs, white sugar and cinnamon. Pour on top of crust.

title: innovative bread
directions: *Experiment.
Combine 2 or more choices.
Be creative.
Try something new (add 1/4 cup peanut butter, etc.).

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil the chicken; drain and cut up.
Cook the spaghetti according to the package directions.
Combine all of the ingredients and put in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich(for mike patterson)
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread followed by jam. Top with other slice of bread!

title: vegetable soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients except macaroni.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer approximately 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni and cook approximately 15 minutes longer or until macaroni is cooked.

title: pizza square
directions: Mix all together, then add shredded Mozzarella cheese and 1 bag of sliced pepperoni and on top sprinkle oregano over the top. Pour into pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: soy mayonnaise
directions: Blend in blender, soy milk, garlic and salt until smooth. Pour in oil very slowly while blending.
Blend until becomes creamy.
Pour into bowl, add the 1/4 cup lemon juice and fold in gradually until thickened.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs well.
Add oil and beat.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda and add to mixture.
Add salt, then beat.
Add pumpkin and beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in three
9-inch layer pans.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put lemon pepper on chicken.
Butter baking dish.
Pour rice mixture in bottom.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Pour mushroom soup and 1 can water (mix) over chicken.
Bake at 350°.
After baking 15 minutes, stir up rice and chicken.
If it gets too dry, add a little water.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan melt 1 cup butter; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Chill shortening. Cut into dry ingredients. Add milk. Knead a few times.
Roll 3/4-inch thick. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes (ungreased sheet).

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and put in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix in 1 can tomato sauce and oregano; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir baking mix, egg and milk into a soft dough.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and allow to cool in fridge for a while.
Use with a platter of sliced fruit.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Make a nice rich pastry dough.
Cut in 5 or 6-inch squares. Place some cooked apples in and fold over.
Moisten edges to make them stick together.
Fry in deep fat at about 370° until done. They will be puffed and brown when done.
Drain on paper towels to get rid of grease.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add sour milk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and stir.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Cook at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes or in 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add topping immediately after cake is removed from oven.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and beat until light.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add egg mixture.
Fold in apples,
nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased dish (square or small oblong dish). Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown in skillet in small amount of oil.
Brown well.
Remove pork chops from pan and add chopped onion, garlic and green bell pepper. Cook until slightly brown. Add consomme, water and rice.
Place pork chops on top and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix ham and cheese together in a bowl. Put mixture on a tray and form into a ball. Put in refrigerator until firm. Serve with crackers.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large heavy boiler brown ground chuck and drain well. Stir in taco and ranch dressing mixes and stir well.
Add Rotel, hominy and beans and stir.

Add diced tomatoes if you want them. Heat to a simmer and it is ready to serve but it is better if you simmer it for a few minutes; or you can put it in a slow cooker. This soup is very thick and very good.

title: irene's pea salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the salad dressing, lightly. Stir in diluted salad dressing.
Chill before serving.
Serves 10.

title: mamie eisenhower's million dollar fudge(original)
directions: Stir together in a saucepan the sugar, butter and milk.
Boil 6 minutes.
Place the semi-sweet bits, sweet chocolate (broken up) and Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl.
Pour the boiling syrup over the mixture of chocolate and marshmallows and beat and stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in nuts and pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Let stand a few hours.
Cut into squares. Makes 5 1/2 pounds.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool mix.
In large bowl, place the cup of starter; add cooled milk mixture.
Stir in flour to make a pliable dough.
Knead 1 to 2 minutes on floured board.
Put in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until double. Punch down and shape into round ball.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Shape into loaf pan that has been greased.
Makes 2 loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan or double boiler over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly onto waxed paper in an 8 x 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel paper off.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: amy stropes' rye bread or biscuits
directions: For breads (makes four loaves), add water to lard, salt and sugars; mix.
Combine molasses and yeast-water and add to first mixture.
Add rye flour and enough white flour to knead dough stiff, but slightly sticky.
Put in bowl.
Let raise in warm place until double in bulk.
Knead on floured board and form into four loaves.
Place in flour greased bread pans.
Prick with fork.
Let raise again and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar; continue to beat.
Add oil and margarine.
Beat well until smooth and creamy.
Cook raisins, reserving 3/4 cup water.
Sift flour and seasonings together. Alternately add flour mixture and water.
Blend well each time. Add raisins and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mmmmm good!

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let stand until firm.
Whip jello thoroughly.
Add pineapple, sour cream and nuts.
Whip all together; pour into mold.
Set away to harden.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Using a small double boiler on a bowl in hot water, carefully melt the chocolate with the oil.
Stir until smooth. Use firm, fresh strawberries.
Be sure they are very dry.
Put chocolate in a cup; dip the strawberries.
Put on covered (wax paper) cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator to harden the chocolate.

title: quick and easy torte
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Top with a can of pie filling.
Chill until set (at least 4 hours).
This recipe is for the woman in a hurry!

title: sweet sugar-free pickles
directions: For each half gallon of pickles, use 3 to 4 tablespoons of sweetener, 1/2 teaspoon alum, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon pickle spices.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Combine other ingredients. Pour over carrots and marinate overnight.
Dip carrots out of sauce to serve.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together in same pan in which to bake.
Use a fork and mix ingredients together.
Do not use a mixer and do not beat. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: the best chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, vanilla, egg yolks, butter, flour and cocoa (sifted together).
Cook on low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Cover with meringue and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: new england blueberry grunt
directions: In heavy covered 3-4 qt. saucepan cook blueberries, sugar, spices, water and lemon juice for 3 minutes over medium heat. Set aside. In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Stir in 1/2 c. milk.
Dough should slide from spoon.
Add more milk if necessary. Drop by Tbsp. (not touching) over blueberries.
Simmer 15-20 minutes. To serve, spoon dumplings into bowls. Top with blueberries. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: l. b. squash pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Allow to stand for 1 hour.
Heat all other ingredients to a boil. Pack squash mixture in clean jars.
Pour hot mixture over squash and seal jars.
Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Dill weed may be added for variety.

title: canadian pork pie
directions: Brown pork in skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in water, onion, bread crumbs, salt, sage, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer, covered until onion is tender for about 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: west virginia summer stew
directions: Cut up first four ingredients in small pieces.
Cut onions into small pieces.
Put oleo and oil in skillet.
Start cooking.
Cut up potatoes into small pieces and cook.
When done, pour off water, add to the skillet with the cooked vegetables until done.
Hot pepper can be added to taste.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil fryers until tender, then remove bones.
Mix all ingredients, except dressing and margarine, together and place in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix dressing and margarine together with pepper, if desired, in frying pan and spread on top of casserole.

title: very good chicken dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake in loaf pan at 400° until done. Combine with 2 to 3 slices white loaf bread.
Season with celery, salt and onion.
Add broth; bake at 400° until done.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut loaf of bread in half lengthwise.
Mix cheese, margarine and seasoning.
Spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: veal stew with red wine
directions: Cut meat into 12 chunks; roll each in 1/2 slice of bacon. Dredge meat lightly with flour.
Melt in heavy skillet 2 tablespoons bacon or fat.
Add meat and onions.
Stir ingredients and permit to brown on all sides.
Remove from pan, pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Add and stir until smooth, consomme and wine.
Add veal and onions. Simmer ingredients closely covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Season and serve with baked dish.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add sugar to cranberry juice cocktail; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Put in freezer to make mixture slushy, stirring occasionally while freezing. When ready to serve, put into punch bowl.
Add the 7-Up or ginger ale.
Serves 32 punch cups.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients
together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Add chips.
Spread in a 15 x 11-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and put into a quart jar with tight fitting lid. Put vinegar and other ingredients into saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain and discard spices.
Pour hot liquid over eggs and put lid on tightly. Refrigerate for 2 days for best flavor.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix well by hand.
Bake on hot griddle 400°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into 4 pieces.
Place on waxed paper or board. Pound flour into it.
If you do not have a mallet, use edge of a saucer.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Brown meat.
Add soup and all other ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer slowly until meat is tender, adding more soup, if necessary.
Cook about 1 hour.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Serves 6.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: quickie cupcakes
directions: Place flour, sugar, shortening and 1/3 cup milk in mixer and blend.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add 1/3 cup milk last.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Yield:
12 cupcakes.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour and pecans.
Melt margarine and pour over flour-pecan mixture.
Pat in bottom of pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: shoney pie
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thickened.
Slice strawberries and put in bottom of baked crust.
Pour cooled mixture over top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: karla's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator to let flavors blend.

title: simple as one two three easy as a.b.c. fudge
directions: In a
heavy
saucepan
over
low
heat, melt chips with condensed milk.
Remove from heat.	Stir in remaining ingredients and spread	evenly in an 8 or 9-inch square pan which has been greased with
butter
or sprayed with Pam.	Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut	into
squares.	Store
in loosely covered container at room temperature.

title: hot sauce
directions: Simmer tomatoes; add other ingredients one at a time.
After adding cilantro, bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Put in a blender and chop to your preference.
May keep in fridge or put in freezer.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl. In a large skillet, brown 1 pound ground beef. Drain. Add 2/3 cup water, the spices and seasonings. Mix thoroughly. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Fix tacos with desired toppings.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat cream cheese and sugar with mixer in a large bowl until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir in 1 2/3 cups small chocolate chips.
Pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 250°.
Bake for 30 minutes. Remove from oven to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Cover; refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Place 1/3 cup chocolate chips and whipping cream in microwave-safe bowl.
Heat on High 20 to 30 seconds.
Cool slightly.
Spread over top of cheese pie. Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, and water in saucepan.
Using whisk, mix well and add egg yolks.
Cook until mixture boils 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Blend in margarine, juice, and rind, if desired.
Let cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or cool whip.

title: greer's chili
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and green pepper lightly in a large skillet and drain. Put in crock-pot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir. Set on low. Cook 8 hours or overnight or set on high and cook 3 hours.
Stir occasionally. Serve with crackers, salad and cheese wedges.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour soups over rice.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Brush chicken with butter.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat egg in bowl or container.
Add 1/2 cup oil; beat again. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Brush liberally on chicken while barbecuing.

title: mother's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen or fryer until tender.
Remove from broth and cool. Debone and set aside.
Save the broth!

title: "old fashioned plain cheesecake"
directions: Spread rolls in bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix all remaining ingredients together and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. After removing from oven, sprinkle cinnamon over cake.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Bring broth boil.
Mix flour, soda, salt, shortening and buttermilk.
Roll out thin on a floured board.
Cut in squares or strips.
Cook by layers in boiling broth, then add milk and cooked, deboned chicken pieces.
I use a 5 or 6 pound hen.

title: fluff
directions: Mix together.
Add fruit of your choice.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: almond toast
directions: 1. Layer spring form pan (big) with toast.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In
a
large
mixing
bowl,
stir together flour, oats, baking powder,
cinnamon
and
salt.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, margarine or butter and brown sugar. Add
to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour batter onto grids of a preheated, lightly greased waffle baker.
Close lid quickly.
Do not
open
during
baking.
Use a fork to remove baked
waffle. Top
with fruit and yogurt.
Makes 12 (4-inch) square waffles, 6 servings.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake crosswise twice.
Remove top two layers. On top of the bottom layer, place softened ice cream (flavor of your choice).
Then place another layer of cake and spread softened ice cream on top.
Top with remaining layer of cake.
Frost the cake with Cool Whip.
Place ice cream cake in the freezer until ready to serve.
For a special treat, use chocolate ice cream and frost cake with chocolate Cool Whip.
Makes a great summer dessert!

title: tuna-roni
directions: Boil water and fix macaroni as written on box.
Drain. Combine vegetables, tuna, cream of mushroom soup and cheese sauce from macaroni in a large saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add macaroni and cook on stove top until well heated.
Season and serve.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Beat sifted powdered sugar and eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Add nuts. Pour in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Set aside.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain grease off. Add tomatoes and macaroni to ground beef mixture.
Simmer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma mickelson's waffles(the best)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and then mix into the rest of the batter.

title: souper burgers
directions: Fry ground beef; drain.
Add minestrone soup and tomato paste; heat through.
Fill hot dog rolls and put sharp shredded cheese on each one.
Put in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: cheese sauce to make any vegetable palatable to kids
directions: Melt over low heat and stir until well mixed.
Pour over cooked vegetables and serve.
One recipe is enough for 2 or 3 meals of vegetables.
Put in a sealed container and it will keep at least a week in the fridge for the next "unacceptable" plain vegetable.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You may use any pie filling.

title: diamond gems
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Shape and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When done, roll each in powdered sugar and let cool.

title: ambrosia no. 2
directions: Combine and chill for one hour before serving.

title: lentils
directions: Measure a cup of lentils; put in a pot of water. Bring to a boil; add celery, garlic and carrot. Let it cook about 2 hours. Boil macaroni. When macaroni is cooked al dente (not mushy), combine it with the lentil mixture. Add grated Romano cheese and enjoy.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart mixing bowl; chill. Serves 8.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls and bake in 300° oven.
They bake more evenly on glass dishes.

title: crumb baked spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook spinach by package instructions. Drain and press to remove water. Place back into pan and add light cream cheese. Stir over low heat until melted. Beat spinach mixture together with eggs, egg whites, milk, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Lightly spray a 9 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Spoon 1/2 of spinach mixture into pan. Then top with 3/4 of the cracker crumbs. Place remainder of spinach mixture on top of crumbs, then top with cheese and remaining crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes, until puffed and golden brown.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix well in bowl beef, onion, bran, bread crumbs, salt, sauce and pepper.
Stir in tomato juice, egg and herbs.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Put all ingredients in iron frying pan (9-inch).
Cook until sugar crystallizes on nuts.
Reduce heat and stir constantly with a heavy spoon as sugar melts on nuts.
Turn on a large greased platter; separate in small clusters or individual nuts as soon as cool enough to handle.
Yields 1 pound.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix yeast and warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and warm milk.
Stir well.
Add eggs and stir.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Place in greased bowl and cover with towel and let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Roll out about 1/2 to 1 inch thick.
Spread soft oleo on dough, thick.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll from long side like jelly roll.
Slice and place on cookie sheet and let rise (covered) for 30 minutes.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ice with a thin powdered sugar icing.

title: salad from arlene
directions: Dissolve lemon and lime jello in just 1 cup boiling water for both and least set.
Beat after jello sets awhile.
Then fold in rest of ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix with Progresso bread crumbs and corn bread and chopped eggs in a large bowl.
Add broth and seasonings and mix, then add raw eggs.
Mix well.
Bake covered in a greased baking pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove foil last few minutes to brown lightly. Gravy is made from leftover broth.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chopped pecans and coconut mixed together.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and melted butter. Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and cut in squares.

title: peanut sauce
directions: Process all ingredients in a food processor.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated, but best served at room temperature.
If too thick, add a little more oil.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls into hot, broiling broth of chicken or beef or your choice.
Turn on low to medium heat to continue boiling.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Do not peek! These never fail.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 circles from bread slices with large doughnut cutter; set aside.
Fit the scraps of bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place cheese in a layer over bread.
Add a layer of broccoli, then ham.
Arrange bread circles on top.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 55 minutes. For a pretty finish, sprinkle with shredded cheese 5 minutes before end of baking time.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water.
Place butter, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add boiling water to ingredients in bowl. When butter melts, add cold water, eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Put into well-greased bowl, cover and store in refrigerator. Make up rolls as needed, shaping and allowing them to double in bulk.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice and sherbet.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sliced bananas and drained oranges.
Set and serve!

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour and mix.
Add milk slowly. Bring to a boil, stir constantly and add corn and sugar.
Season to taste.
Add eggs. Mix thoroughly.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except buttermilk in food processor or mixer.
Add buttermilk, forming dough.
Roll dough on floured area, not too thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Biscuits can be frozen.
Put on tray overnight or until hard.
Place in plastic bag and freeze.
Use as needed. Bake frozen biscuits at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Soak overnight in cold water (enough to cover).
Drain beans; combine with 6 cups water in pan. Bring to a boil and simmer 45 minutes until beans are firm tender.
Drain beans, reserving water.
Cut up pork.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart bowl.
Pour enough bean water to cover. Bake covered in slow oven (275°) for 3 hours.
Uncover; bake 2 hours more.
Stir beans occasionally and add water as needed. Serves 6.

title: potato salad(patatas alinadas)
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes (whole) until soft.
Boil eggs until hard-boiled.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Peel potatoes and dice.
Add diced green pepper, tomato, chopped onions and chopped egg.
Add oil, vinegar and salt.
Serve immediately.

title: nantua sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar; shake well. Refrigerate to store.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: half and half pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add egg yolks, two at a time.
Fold in flour and stiffly beaten egg whites and cream.
Beat slowly and bake at 300° to 350° until brown.
Makes one pound cake.

title: colache(kolache)
directions: In some oil, steam until fork-tender the bell pepper and onion and remaining ingredients.
Cover and let simmer, not soupy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Take from refrigerator and mix in Part 2 with Part 1 ingredients.

title: speedy spicy chili
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef, onion, garlic and chili powder until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in beans, soup, chilies and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the bouillon cube.
Mix all ingredients together. Add a little plain gelatin to jello to be sure it congeals.
Let chill before serving.

title: my barbecued chicken
directions: This recipe will be by "your" taste.
Put cut up chicken in casserole.
Mix barbecue sauce, catsup (rinse barbecue bottle with Coke).
Put all together with brown sugar.
Pour over chicken and bake for one hour at 375°.
Fix with boiled rice.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flours, salt and soda.
Add chopped apples last.
Bake in a loaf pan for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans. Stir until all ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool in pans for 5 minutes.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, walnuts and flour.
Stir in butter and mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press the rest into an 8-inch square pan and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat cheese with sugar.
Beat in the egg.
Add the lemon juice, milk and vanilla. Blend.
Pour onto baked crust. Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes. Cool and chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour until smooth.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks slightly.
Combine sugar and flour mixture, egg yolks, milk, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, so mixture won't stick to pan.
Cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until sauce is very thick.
Layer pan with vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour cooled sauce over cookies and sliced bananas.
Layer cookies and bananas until pan is full, ending with cookies on top.
Sprinkle with crumbled vanilla wafers and sugar.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Let stand 5 minutes.

Beat egg yolks and sugar until light and fluffy. Add lemon juice and lemon rind. Blend carefully. Melt gelatin with water over low heat. Add to egg mixture, stirring well. Whip the cream. Fold cream into egg mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into egg mixture.
Pour mousse into 4 serving bowls. Chill in refrigerator for about 2 1/2 hours. Garnish mousse with lemon peel and whipped cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat off meat.
Rub steak on both sides with cut clove of garlic.
Pound into it a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak against grain into thick strips about 2-inches long.
Peel onion and cut it into small pieces.
In a heavy frying pan, brown onion in some of the trimmed off beef fat.
Remove onion with slotted spoon.
Brown meat quickly in the same fat; return onion to pan and heat.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 15 minutes.
Meat should be quite tender.
If you use a lesser cut of meat, it will take a little longer.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
Serves 6 appetites.

title: simple fish casserole
directions: Spread butter on bottom of shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add spinach and cover with fish fillets.
Season lightly with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add onion and spread soup on top. Arrange tomato slices on top of soup and sprinkle with oregano. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: boston creme torte
directions: Prepare
pudding
as
directed,
reducing milk to 2 1/2 cups. Chill.
Split cake making 4 layers.
Beat pudding until creamy; spread between the layers.	Melt chocolate and butter in a	pan over
low
heat.
Combine sugar, milk and salt in a bowl.
Add chocolate; beat until smooth.
Spread over the top of the cake.

title: chicken delight
directions: Take chicken breasts, remove skin and debone.
Place in medium size baking dish that has been buttered.
Place bacon strips across chicken.
Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Mix thoroughly and spread over chicken.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll thin and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Mix egg, margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, baking soda and flour.
Refrigerate while you make your icing.

title: special southern pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and eggs.
Add 1 stick melted and cooled butter.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Bake pie shell four minutes at 400° before filling.
Fill shell and bake at 325° for one hour.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: quick pecan coffee ring
directions: In a metal ring mold or a cake pan with a tin can placed in the center, break pecans into pieces and place in the bottom of pan, spreading evenly.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter, then roll in sugar mixture and stand on edge in pan on top of pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven, place a serving plate on top and invert.
Let stand a few minutes before removing the pan.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a ring mold pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Combine apple with cinnamon and 1/4 cup of sugar; set aside.
Mix remaining sugar with all remaining ingredients.
Pour layer of batter into mold, then layer of apples and repeat, finishing with apples last.
Bake 1 3/4 hours and allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: apple-cheese flan
directions: Combine first three ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Mix in grated cheese and work until mixture forms a dough.
Roll out onto floured surface to a 12-inch circle.
Slide onto baking sheet and fold up edge to make 1/2-inch border or fit into a 10-inch tart pan.

title: onion cake
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon; discard pan drippings.
In same skillet, cook onions in margarine until tender.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, combine sour cream, flour, salt and eggs.
Stir in bacon and onions; set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni.
Drain and add rest of ingredients with chopped Spam and mix.

title: salmon dip
directions: Blend all together very well and serve on crackers.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and pour liquids into it. Mix only long enough to mix dry ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: rice and bean salad
directions: Drain beans; mix all ingredients.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 16.

title: sunflower soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, whole wheat flour, cornmeal, sunflower seeds, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and egg; beat until dough is thoroughly moistened and stretchy, about 2 minutes.
Spoon dough in 2 equal mounds, each on center of a 10 x 15-inch pan.
With floured hands, pat each portion into an 8-inch round.
With a floured sharp knife, cut a 1/2-inch deep cross on top of each round.
Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Switch pan positions after 15 minutes. Serve warm or cool; cut into wedges.
To store, wrap airtight when cool.
Hold at room temperature up until next day, or freeze. Makes 2 loaves, each about 1 1/3 pounds.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and spread in greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until butter is melted and pour over date mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brisket
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar, pepper, ketchup and garlic for marinade.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Stir butter until creamy; add sugar gradually.
Add well beaten eggs and flavoring.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk to the first mixture.
Pour batter into 8 x 8-inch pan and sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Brown in skillet the hamburger, onion and green pepper. Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste. Stir in tomato sauce. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cold oven. Turn to 350°. Cook for 1 hour.
Great served with whipped topping.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in order, then fold in by hand Rice Krispies, coconut and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These have to be watched closely so as not to burn.

title: goody cookies
directions: Mix
butter and powdered sugar together.
Add flour and flavorings.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel banana and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Put milk, vanilla and frozen banana pieces in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Yield: 2 servings.
Contains 95 calories per serving.

title: mexican squash
directions: Melt margarine in pan; saute onions, celery, bell pepper and sliced squash on top of stove.
Cook medium to high until squash begins to look clear.
