Add salt, pepper, cumin, garlic and tomatoes.
Place lid on and simmer until squash is medium soft. Remove lid and add cheese and replace lid until cheese melts.
Can be frozen.
Serves 10.

title: kevin's hamburger helper
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Bake in greased 8 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: roasted potatoes(deliciously browned and seasoned potatoes)
directions: Put all ingredients in a paper or plastic bag and shake to distribute over potatoes.
Pour into an uncovered casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: nutty gingerbread
directions: In large mixing bowl combine sugar, shortening and molasses. Add eggs and beat well with wooden spoon.
Stir together dry ingredients and nuts and add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Stir in water.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook in iron skillet or heavy pan until mixture is toffee colored (about 10 to 12 minutes over medium-high heat, stirring constantly).
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan so toffee will be about 1/4-inch thick.
Across the hot candy, lay 3 small Hershey bars.
When chocolate melts, spread smooth.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix. Spoon on top of salad and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Then mix it up with 1 head lettuce, cut fine, just before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: rice krispies oatmeal
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add salt, baking powder, soda and flour. Add walnuts, Rice Krispies and quick oats.
Drop on cookie sheet with a teaspoon.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: snow white 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler.
Beat 1 minute with electric mixer or rotary beater. Place over boiling water.
Beat constantly until frosting forms peaks, about seven minutes.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla; beat until of spreading consistency, about 2 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli cheese meal
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cook broccoli to directions.
Mix all together and cook until cheese melts.
Serve over rice.

title: butterscotch yule log
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water.
Remove, stir in condensed milk and vanilla; add chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until firm enough to handle. Form into 12-inch roll on waxed paper.
Roll tightly in waxed paper to shape evenly.

title: steamed carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend on low.
Beat at medium 2 minutes.
Turn into greased, floured 6-cup Bundt pan. Set wok on high heat (350°).
Bring 2 cups water to boil in wok; position rack in wok.
Place Bundt pan on rack; cover wok, lower heat to slow boil.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Leave in a roll in icebox overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 or 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: cranberry apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grate the orange peel and set aside. Squeeze orange. You will need 1/2 cup juice. Cream shortening in mixing bowl. Add eggs and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and sugar together. Stir in orange peel. Add flour mixture, milk and orange juice alternately to shortening. Stir well after each addition. Batter will be stiff. Fold in blueberries. Grease small muffin cups or use paper liners. Fill each 1/2 full of batter. Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 20 minutes or until browned. Yield: About 24 small muffins.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Boil 1 c. water in sauce pan. Remove from heat and add butter. Stir until melted, add sugar and salt to this and stir until dissolved. Cool to luke warm.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray and flour a tube pan.
In large bowl, add sugar, shortening, flavors and eggs.
Beat and then add flour gradually.
Add soda and salt.
Beat and then add the buttermilk.
Stir and add bananas and pecans.
Beat well.
Pour into tube pan.
You will have a little leftover, so you can pour that into a little bread pan (make sure it is greased and floured). Bake both for 1 hour in the oven.

title: aunt margaret's pot pie
directions: Take a pot roast and put it in a pot.
Add enough water to half cover the roast.
Do not brown the roast as this will make a dark gravy.

title: sukiyaki
directions: In a large pot, combine bouillon cubes and water.
Heat until cubes dissolve.
Add molasses, spices, oil and flour.
Stir and heat until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over fairly high heat, stirring, for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool and remove meat from bones.
Place cut-up chicken in a lightly buttered oblong baking dish.
Mix together soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Toss crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves approximately 6.

title: punch
directions: In large container, put presugared Kool-Aid, water per package, orange juice with water per container and pineapple juice and blend all together.
Scoop out lime sherbet; pour juice over together with ginger ale.
Serves about 35 people (4 ounces).
Put in large punch bowl.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cook chicken; bone and cut up. Layer in a baking dish the chicken, onion and cheese with tortillas. Mix soups, chicken broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chili powder together. Pour mixture over ingredients in baking dish. Top dish with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Cook onions before using.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling for about 5 minutes over medium heat until it forms soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Add vanilla. Pour into pan lined with wax paper. Cool and cut into squares.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add water and cocoa and bring to boil. Mix together in large mixing bowl remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture.

title: party casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, then stir in milk and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin with hot water and cranberry sauce.
Stir in orange pieces and pecans.
Chill in individual molds or in pan to be cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, syrup and salt; cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat well and pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares before it completely hardens.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, eggs, mayonnaise, milk, salt, soda and spices in large bowl.
Add raisins, nuts, apples and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and pat in pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: cream of chicken with cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter for about 10 minutes.
Add chicken stock and simmer until vegetables are tender (about 15 minutes). Add cream and heat to simmering.
Add cheese and chicken, stirring to melt cheese.
Season to taste.
Heat through and serve, garnished with parsley.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add soups, tomatoes, enchilada sauce mix and 1 cup of water.
Simmer until bubbly.

title: aunt rosy's dessert
directions: Allow ice cream and cream cheese to soften slightly.
Blend together with electric mixer.
Stir in whipped cream and put mixture in Oreo crust.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with frozen or fresh raspberries.

title: pumpkin cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Add butter.
Mix well until crumbly.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325°.

title: polish chrusciki
directions: Mix 4 cups flour, 4 tablespoons Crisco, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons baking powder with 1 cup sugar.
Beat 3 eggs and vanilla. Add to the mixture.
Take the dough and knead on the flour board until firm and smooth enough to roll.
Cut into 4-inch strips; slit in the center and pull one end through.
Fry in deep grease until brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Add bacon bits, onion, vinegar, catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard. Cook together for 10 minutes. Add the 3 varieties of beans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or cook in crock-pot for 1 hour on high.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with cauliflower, celery, broccoli, carrots, green onion, squash or turnips.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mash cheese and add other ingredients.

title: cherry brown betty
directions: Put pie filling in glass pan.
Mix dry items together.
Pour melted butter in dry items.
Mix well.
Put on top of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: almond green beans
directions: Fry bacon. Use drippings and add vinegar, sugar, onion and almonds. Add drained beans. Simmer about 40 minutes. Crumble bacon on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma's raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Pour in pie shell; pat with butter and cover with pie shell top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until golden brown.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate steak for 6 hours or overnight. Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat.
Broil, brushing with marinade. Turn occasionally.
Carve in thin slices diagonally across grain of meat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar gradually and mix well.
Beat the eggs into the creamed ingredients.
Add sifted dry ingredients and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat egg rolls
directions: Combine
cornstarch,
salt,
soy sauce and sherry.
Set aside. Heat
wok or wide frying pan over high heat.
When pan is hot, add
salad	oil.
When oil begins to heat, add garlic and
ginger. Stir.
Add
onion	and
celery
and
stir-fry
1 minute.
Add meat,
bamboo
shoots and cabbage and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir cornstarch	mixture
and
add to pan and cook, stirring until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Cool.	Brush edges of wrapper	with lightly beaten egg after filling center with meat filling.	Roll and fold into elongated shape.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Remove and drain excess oil.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add almond extract.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased tube pan.
Add cranberry sauce.
Add rest of batter and swirl with knife.
Sprinkle with nuts (pat in).
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool well in pan.

title: sarah's pizza casserole
directions: *Do not cook prior to putting in casserole, as these should be crunchy.

title: aunt zelma's apple dumplings
directions: Depends on how many dumplings you want.
You use 1/2 per dumpling.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Season ground chuck with salt and pepper.
Saute meat and eggplant in oil on medium heat until done and moist.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook on low heat about 30 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Add cooked rice.
Cover; simmer on low heat for ten minutes.
You may wish to add seasoning to adjust taste.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: eskimo cookie
directions: Melt in big pan.
Add 2 cups quick oats.
Place in refrigerator until hard enough to roll into ball.
If you want, leave plain or roll in powdered sugar.

title: spicy spud chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 9 x 13 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place the melted butter in shallow dish. In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients except chicken.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then potato mixture, coating well. (I use gallon storage bag to shake it in.)

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add saute to beef and mix well.
Add green pepper, egg, seasonings and remaining ingredients. Mix. Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add catsup to top of meat loaf if desired, then bake 40 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milky way wonder cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick margarine together; set aside. Cool.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Mix vanilla into batter well.
Blend in candy mix and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in 3 greased and floured pans.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sundried tomato dip(yield: 2 cups)
directions: 1. Puree the tomatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, tabasco sauce, salt and pepper in a food processor fitted with a metal blade.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix eggs, rice, ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper. Form small meat balls and bake 1/2 hour at 350° on a cookie sheet. Heat ketchup and grape jelly on top of stove until melted and add brown sugar and Worcestershire, simmer 20 minutes. Pour sauce over meat balls to serve.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Finely crush 1 package graham crackers and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium bowl, mix pudding and milk according to directions. Fold in Cool Whip and blend well.
Spread over crumbs.
Break second package of grahams in half.
Form layer over pudding.
Place frosting in small microwave bowl and microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds, stirring once or twice.
Pour over crackers.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Set aside and let set boiling water, chopped dates and soda. Cream together butter, Crisco, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour, cocoa and salt and mix.
Add last dates, water and soda mixture and blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips and nuts over top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ladyfinger cookies
directions: Place all ingredients together and make finger-size cookies. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° close to the top of oven until brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and roll in 4x powdered sugar.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh relishes or vegetables.

title: peanut butter cheese ball
directions: Beat together peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; add milk as necessary to make smooth.
Roll in peanuts.
Chill several hours.
Serve with apple wedges or whole wheat crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Add 1 can of pie filling.
Pour dry cake mix over filling. Spread pecans over cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange gumdrop chews
directions: Beat eggs with water until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and salt, beating until light and fluffy.
Thoroughly mix candy, coconut, nuts and flour.
Stir into egg mixture.
Spread into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool; cut in bars or squares.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: ragu sauce
directions: Mix together in frying pan the ground beef, sliced onion, green pepper, bacon, salt and pepper.
Add garlic; cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: strawberry and sour cream supreme
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add other ingredients and congeal half of mixture.
When congealed, spread sour cream on top.
Then pour remaining half of mixture and congeal.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Chop wings in half and remove wing tips.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown seasoned chicken in 1/4 cup of oil in frying pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: festive corn bread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: almond apricot tartlets
directions: Dough:
Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in butter to make small peas.
Add egg yolk and water; stir with fork.
Press into small muffin cups.
Chill while making filling.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and vanilla.
Stir in pureed fruit.
Fold in 2 cups (1 pint) whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch long pan.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours.

title: penny sweet pickles
directions: Cover pickles with salt and water.
Let stand 3 days.
Drain and cover with water and add alum.
Bring to a boil and drain again.
Cover with water and add ginger.
Boil again and drain. Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, cloves and cinnamon.
Boil 1/2 hour and can.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger in large saucepan.
Add chili powder, cumin and pepper; mix well.
Place tomatoes with juice in separate bowl. Mash to desired consistency.
Add to meat and mix well.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Just prior to serving cut up fresh condiments.
Heat vegetable oil in small pan and deep fry corn tortillas (use fresh flour tortillas for a lower fat version).
Spoon sauce over tortillas; add condiments as desired and serve.
Add less chili powder and pepper for a milder version of this dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, and marshmallow cream. Once well blended add Cool Whip.

title: lemon pecan sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, combine sugars, margarine, ReaLemon and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Reserving 1/4 cup, pour remaining ReaLemon mixture into 9-inch round layer cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: coconut cookies(icebox)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Form into rolls (1 1/2-inches in diameter).
Chill again.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 325°.
Slice cookies and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Keep an eye on first sheet after 8 minutes to check brownness.
Should just be brown on edges.

title: gerri's cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and stir.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend all ingredients together except chocolate wafers in large bowl.
(Mix does get hard to blend.)
After Mixing form into balls. refrigerate until firm.
Take chocolate wafers and melt in double boiler.
Be careful not to scorch chocolate.
Take the chilled candy with toothpicks and dip into chocolate.
Place on wax paper to settle.
You have to work quickly or reheat the chocolate. Remove toothpicks and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients into a bottle and shake well.
Good on salads or sliced tomatoes and onions.

title: kathy's fabulous fruit dip
directions: Combine marshmallow and cream cheese in a bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Add a dash of cherry juice to color.
Serve with pieces of fruit.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add milk and sugar; mix well.
Pour in a buttered casserole dish and put 2 1/2 slices bread on top.
Let bread soak up and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until nice browned and a knife comes out clean.
Eat warm or cold.

title: ricotta pie (two)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. No top shells needed.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour to make dough.
Put in large bowl.
Flour and knead like biscuits.
Roll and cut like biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter in a 2-quart glass bowl. Cover with a paper towel and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press mixture into an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Combine chocolate morsels and shortening in a 2-cup glass measure; microwave at Medium (50% power) 2 minutes or until chocolate melts.
Spread over peanut butter mixture. Chill and cut into squares.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Cook zucchini in a large saucepan, covered with boiling salted water until crisp and tender (5 minutes).
Drain well.
Saute onion and green pepper in oleo until tender.
Stir in sauce and spices. Heat through.
Separate egg yolk and white.
Chop white.
Add zucchini.
Use 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2 inch dish.
Line with a little sauce, layer of zucchini, 1/2 of sauce, cheese, 1/2 of sauce and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine in large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup margarine.
Season with salt and pepper and add onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend ingredients thoroughly; pour into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Mix remaining margarine with cornflakes.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 12 to 15 servings.
Note: You may also add 2 cups cooked ham (diced) or chicken (diced) to this recipe.
It also freezes well.

title: raspberry and honey tilapia
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 11 x 7 inch baking dish and arrange the tilapia filets in a single layer in the prepared dish. Whisk together all ingredients (except fish) and pour mixture over the fish filets, coating the filets evenly. Bake in a preheated oven, uncovered for 20 minutes or until fish is flaky with a fork.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach well (squeeze out the water).
Mix all ingredients well and let set overnight.
Serve with crackers or small rye bread.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix all and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: dale's chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan combine first 6 ingredients.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Beat until marshmallows are melted.
(This makes the filling very creamy.)
Spoon into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut meat into four pieces; pound meat until tender.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together in a pie pan.
Dredge steak in flour mixture.
Cook in hot melted shortening or oil over medium or high heat until brown.
Turn and brown on other side.
The quicker the meat cooks, the juicer it stays.
Don't overcook steak.
Make a cream gravy.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Line 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with chilies; put grated cheese over chilies.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper. Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate overnight pasta and salad dressing.
Mix with other ingredients and serve.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: company's comin' cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs and add applesauce and water.
Add dry ingredients, then stir in nuts and raisins.
Place into well-greased wide mouth canning pint jars.
Place only half full (do not put in more than half full).
Make sure edges of jar stay clean.
Place evenly on cookie sheet and put into 325° oven; do not let jars touch.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Check with cake tester.
Open oven door and remove one at a time.
Place on towel on counter and add canning lids and twist closed.
Listen for jars to seal.
Should last for up to a year.
Store as you would regular canned goods. Recipe makes eight pints.
This "canned cake" is great to have waiting on a shelf to serve with coffee when unexpected company drops in.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in greased bowl and cover with wet cloth.
Let rise double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead and form into your favorite shape rolls. Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour. Stir in 3 tablespoons juice. Add pineapple and cheese. Pour into 1-quart casserole. Combine butter and crackers. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes until light golden brown.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mil's sweet potatoes
directions: Clean, peel and chunk sweet potatoes.
Place potatoes in a large heavy skillet (on stove top).
Add 2 cups water, margarine and brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Then turn back to simmer for 1 hour until syrup thickens and potatoes are tender.
Do not cover while cooking.

title: apple cake
directions: Will need a well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips and roll in flour with little salt and pepper added.
Brown meat in oil, then add onion and water. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add soup and sour cream; stir and then simmer until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked noodles. Serves 4.

title: simple alfredo sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine butter, heavy cream and cream cheese. Simmer until all is melted, mix well. Add the parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Simmer at low heat for 15 - 20 minutes. Add salt and pepper, to taste. Let simmer at least 30 - 45 minutes at low heat (the longer the better).

title: squash casserole bake
directions: Slice squash in food processor slicing blade.
Cover squash and margarine with plastic wrap.
Microwave 6 minutes on High. Stop and stir once.

title: oysters kirkpatrick
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons of the butter, then combine with bacon, chili sauce, lemon juice, Marsala and Tabasco sauce. Dot each oyster with remainder of butter, then broil until edges begin to scallop. Top oysters with sauce mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan and continue to broil until mixture begins to bubble and Parmesan browns slightly.

title: lefse
directions: Rice potatoes and add butter, sugar, salt and whipping cream when hot.
Add flour when cold just before rolled out.
Roll thin and fry on grill or lefse plate.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry together hamburger and onion until browned.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour.
Pour meat into a 6-quart kettle; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Ready to serve!

title: kaffee klatsch strawberry jello(delicious!)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add pineapple and strawberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until set.
Put the following topping on the congealed jello.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops and melt in heavy pan until 2 tablespoons collects.
Remove rind.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chops and brown in fat.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch baking pan. Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary in small bowl.
Pour over chops.
Place 1/2 can of onion rings on top. Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until tender. Remove cover and place remaining onion rings on top. Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: cypress inn muffins
directions: Place ingredients in bread machine in order specified by your manufacturer.
Use "Manual" setting and let machine knead, raise, and knead the second time.
Remove from machine and shape into two long rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet or French bread pan and let rise until double in bulk.
(If you're using a cookie sheet, put a long folded piece of foil between the two loaves.)

title: darlene's fruit ambrosia
directions: Whip cream.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows.
Add cream mixture to sour cream mixture.
Drain fruit well on paper towel.
Fold in drained pineapple, then cherries and last carefully fold in oranges.

title: brown county fried biscuits
directions: Sprinkle yeast in the fourth cup of warm water and let dissolve; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and sugar.
Stir in melted shortening, dissolved yeast and milk. Stir until dough is smooth.
Cover bowl with damp cloth and let rise to double in bulk.
Pull off pieces and roll lightly into balls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Drop into hot fat a few at a time. Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side until puffy and browned.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Drain biscuits on paper towel.
Serve immediately with butter and apple butter.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream together the margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add the almond flavoring and flour.
Mix well.
Carefully stir in blueberries. Spread batter in the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
While still warm, drizzle with frosting.

title: roulade(beef rolls)
directions: Beat steaks until thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread mustard on one side (I do not beat meat).
Lay a slice of bacon on top of the mustard on each steak.
Place a pickle at one end of the steak and roll it.
Tie or use pick to keep together. Melt shortening in a roasting pan and brown on all sides of the steak.
Add water.
Cover and cook in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Thicken the sauce with flour.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: curried chicken-fricassee
directions: Salt the chicken parts and fry in butter on all sides in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add curry and onion 5 minutes before the frying is done and fry to a golden brown.
Add the broth; cover and leave to simmer until chicken is cooked.
Cook mushrooms no longer than 10 minutes in this mixture.
Remove chicken and mushrooms.
Add combined flour and milk to liquid to thicken.
Add chicken and mushrooms back to sauce.
Heat thoroughly and serve over rice.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Saute beef, onion and green pepper in oil.
Drain.
Stir in sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients together and drop into greased muffin tins.
Cook at 450° until brown.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except candy kisses.
Blend at low speed to form a stiff dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Press a candy kiss down firmly so cookie cracks.

title: mexicali corn and bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook onions in oil until crisp.
Add beans, corn, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, or until thickened.
Unroll dough and separate twists; cut each twist into thirds.
Pour bean mixture into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place twist pieces on top of hot bean mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until mixture is bubbly and twist pieces are a golden brown.

title: blueberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stir constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Stir in vanilla and lemon juice.
Set mixture aside.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal; add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread blueberries over dough; roll up, jelly roll fashion, beginning with long side.
Set aside.

title: mamma's potato doughnuts
directions: Flavor with vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat potatoes and butter together until well blended.
Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add milk and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cook in hot shortening as you would any other doughnut.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into small pieces.
Mix all together.
Cook in crock-pot for 45 minutes on high, then cook for 5 to 6 hours on low.
Stir when necessary.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer everything in this order.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients, then let the mixture stand while you slice the rest.
Mix together all the vegetables, then add the vinegar mixture.
Let it stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: lemon-dill vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in a plastic container with a lid. Shake very well to emulsify.
Serve over salad greens or as a dip for crisp vegetables.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine corn meal, salt and baking soda.
Stir into corn mixture and pour into lightly greased oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour and salt in double boiler.
Stir in mixture of milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook over hot water until mixture thickens and coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla and cool.

title: jambalaya
directions: *The Tony Chachere's creole seasoning is available at Schnucks and some other stores.

Look around seafood or deli area. In a 8 quart stockpot, put the tomatoes, tomato sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies, mushrooms, parsley, bay leaves, creole seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic.
Cover and put over low heat to simmer.

title: beer barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine until slightly brown. Add remaining ingredients, except beer.
Stir well until blended and then add beer in small amounts, carefully as it will bubble over.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add a little nutmeg to flour and sugar. Add milk and peaches.
Add melted butter.
Cook on 350° until brown.

title: daddy g's jambalaya
directions: Brown smoked sausage in
large
pot.
Remove and drain. In pot, cook onions, green onion tops, bell pepper, garlic and celery over medium heat until tender.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening and lard into flour until coarse like oatmeal. Add baking soda, buttermilk, baking powder and salt.
Turn dough on floured board.
Break or cut into sphere size shapes.
Bake in a 475° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well with hands.
If tough, put a little warm water in it. Roll in ball or logs, then put 3/4 cup chopped walnuts on aluminum foil and roll ball in walnuts.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides in oil in frying pan.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place chops in dish and cover with (uncooked) rice.
Blend soup and milk together and pour over rice.
Be sure to completely cover rice with soup. Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Soup should be absorbed by rice and chops.
Serve with salad. Yum!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick glazed pineapple
directions: Drain canned pineapple.
Dip them in brown sugar.
Brown them by simmering for about 3 to 5 minutes on each side in hot drippings or butter.
You may also dust them with grated cheese and/or a few grains of red pepper and broil or bake them in a moderate oven to melt cheese.

title: sour cream potato salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion and eggs in bowl.
Combine and mix the remaining ingredients.
Add dressing to potato mixture. Mix carefully.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine; add
poppy
seed, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and onion.
Spread
on
both
sides
of rolls which have been split in half
lengthwise.	Add a layer of ham and top with layer of cheese.
Put
top
of rolls over ham and cheese. Bake until cheese melts (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: ranny's cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add one quart of water.
Chop cabbage, carrots, potatoes, and add to celery and onion mixture. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
When vegetables are done, add soups.
Heat and add cheese.
Soup is done when cheese melts.
Makes a lot!

title: tarragon-dijon chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with spray.
Place breasts, flesh side down, in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover snugly with foil, sealing edges.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
During final 10 minutes, remove foil and turn chicken flesh side up.
Remove chicken breasts to serving platter.
Strain juice and spoon over each breast.

title: crullers
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with cream to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place dough on floured board. Pat and roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into 6 x 1-inch strips. Twist dough and press ends together.
Fry a few at a time in deep fryer at 360° until brown. Drain and dust with powdered sugar. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pineapple orange fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: banana nut bread muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in remaining ingredients, adding bananas and nuts last.
Pour mixture into muffin pan sprayed with no-stick.
Bake at 350°
for about 20 minutes.
Use toothpick to test.

title: beefy lentil soup
directions: Brown ground chuck in a 6-quart Dutch oven or kettle over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and 4 cups water.
Cook over high heat until mixture boils, about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until lentils are tender, stirring occasionally. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: annie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Blend in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. (Roll out to desired thickness.)

title: peach delight
directions: Heat gelatin, sugar and pineapple, stirring all the time. Cool.
When cool, add the buttermilk and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold or Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: Melt butter; add wafers.
Line bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, juice and rind.
Stir in butter.
Spread over pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
Boil sugar, margarine, syrup and salt for 5 minutes. Remove from heat, add baking soda.
Stir over popped corn.
Spread in large roasting pan.
Place in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring at 15 minute intervals.
Remove from oven; let cool completely.
Store in covered container.

title: flan(a spanish custard)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour caramelized sugar into a well buttered 9-inch layer cake pan.
Beat egg yolks lightly with sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually mix in hot milk.
Pour into pan.
Set in large, shallow pan and pour in hot water to a 1/2-inch depth.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from water bath and cool to room temperature.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Dip pan quickly in hot water, then invert on serving dish.
Cut into wedges and serve. Contains 270 calories for each 6 servings and 200 calories for each 8 servings.

title: barbara mandrell
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in pan and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Spread chocolate pudding on cream cheese mixture.
Spread vanilla pudding on chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: baked apple turnovers
directions: Cut pastry into eight 4 1/2-inch circles.
Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons apples on one-half of each circle.
Moisten edges with water; fold dough over and crimp edges with fork.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 435° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over cooked turnover.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed until well blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually. Beat constantly, until light and fluffy.
If too stiff, add a little milk.
Season with garlic salt.
Spoon potatoes into a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Can be refrigerated for several days. Reheat at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple flip
directions: Mix wafers and margarine together and pack to form crust in a large glass dish.
Cover mixture with bananas.
Mix lemon juice and milk; spread over bananas.
Drain pineapple and mix with coconut. Spread over ingredients in dish.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add pecans and garnish with cherries.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken; cut up in small pieces and put in casserole dish.
Boil broccoli and drain (don't overcook).
Add to chicken.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and store in container.
To make a cup, use 2 to 4 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice, flour, sugar and butter and cook until mixture coats spoon.
Add pineapple, nuts and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
Add egg.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add a few drops hot water, mix until blended.
Add chopped nuts, semi-sweet chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: seasoned salt blend 1(salt free)
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add grated carrot and green pepper.

title: cheesy asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan on low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add soup and Cheddar cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: elephant stew
directions: This is a very old recipe of unknown origin, but no cookbook should be without it.

title: princess brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Combine cream cheese and sugar and beat until well blended. Stir in vanilla and egg. Spread half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan. Cover with cheese mixture, then spoon on remaining batter. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan, then cut 4 dozen bars.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, lemon peel, juice, then add the egg. Mix well.
Cool until sugar is dissolved and sauce is slightly thickened.
Stir.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Toast pecans with butter and salt.
Mix next 6 ingredients and fold in sour cream and 1/2 nuts.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish with Melba rounds.

title: corn, potatoes and hamburger casserole
directions: Stir-fry hamburger, onion and seasoning (to taste) until browned.
Layer in casserole - first the hamburger, then corn, then mashed potatoes as crust.
Keep in layers.
Do not mix.
Cook at 400° for about 20 minutes, until brown on tips of potatoes.
This is for 2 people, but you can increase meat and potatoes to serve more people.

title: jackie's turkey gravy
directions: Boil turkey necks until done.
Skim off fat, if desired. Debone necks and discard bones.
Brown flour in a skillet; add stock and stir.
Add salt, pepper and turkey meat.
Add water if needed.

title: mildred's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar; add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and bananas. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 65 minutes.

title: chile dip
directions: Mix and melt all in crock-pot.
Serve with your choice of chips.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Place on hamburger buns with chilled lettuce leaf.
(Add 16 ounces cooked, rinsed and chilled macaroni rings if to be used just for salad and serve on a lettuce leaf.) Serves 50.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine meat, juice, onion, seasoning and 6 cups water in kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Cut meat from bones into large cubes.
Strain broth and skim off fat.
Add meat and vegetables to broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain and layer in casserole. Top with finely chopped spinach.
Mix together lightly the tomato juice, basil, oregano, salt, pepper, parsley, mushrooms and cottage cheese.
Spread on top of spinach.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
It doesn't look very pretty, but it is delicious!

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, wash, and cut potatoes in small chunks. Peel, wash, and slice carrots. Peel, wash, and chop onions. Place in big pot and cover with water. Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender. If using bacon, fry bacon crisp, crumble. Add bacon or ham to soup, along with rest of ingredients. Cook for 20 minutes longer.

title: old fashioned chicken stew
directions: In a large pot put broth and chicken.
Crumble up saltines in the broth and chicken.
Add sweet milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Good with hot sauce and catsup.

title: strawberry party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
In large punch bowl combine jello, lemonade, orange juice and cold water.
Just before serving, gently stir in ginger ale and frozen strawberries.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: three-day pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir in milk, flour, sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into mixture.
Pour from 1/4 cup into greased and preheated griddle or electric skillet (use 380° setting on skillet).
Bake until surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn and bake on other side.
Makes 16 pancakes.
Serves 4 to 8 people.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and honey.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Sift together salt and flour.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Raisins and figs are chopped and lightly floured before adding.
Beat a good 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan (greased) in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out dry.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops in baking dish.
Top each chop with 1 slice of onion, 1 slice of American cheese and 1 teaspoon sour cream.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Adjust oven accordingly if seems too hot.

title: garden patch potato salad
directions: Halve any large potato slices.
In a 2-quart bowl, toss together the potatoes, carrots, celery, olives and radishes.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix juices in punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up.

title: shrimp russe
directions: Clean the shrimp totally.
Saute in butter or margarine.
Pour the milk slowly.
Add the ketchup to give it color.
Add garlic. Cook for no more than 5 minutes.
Serve with lemon along with white rice or mashed potatoes and enjoy!

title: pound cake
directions: Start in cold oven.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately. Mix well.
Add flavorings.
Pour in well-greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn onto wire rack to completely cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in hot milk.
Add bread crumbs.
Add all remaining ingredients (but crumbs and cheese) and place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat cherry and pineapple juice together. Add Jello and dissolve. Beat the cream cheese. Mix together all other ingredients. Pour into mold and chill.

title: corn ole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 6.

title: charleston lupus support group recipe
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly for a group of warm, concerned and sharing members.
We welcome you to visit at anytime.

title: my favorite chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Then in a saucepan melt butter, water, oil and cocoa; bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Add 2 bananas, sliced, before serving.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
In a saucepan, combine and bring to a boil the butter, water, shortening and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Combine buttermilk and soda; beat eggs slightly and mix with buttermilk and soda.
Add vanilla.
Add to the other mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch greased and floured pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix thoroughly. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle potato chips or cheese on top. Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, lemon juice or vanilla and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Lightly flour rolling surface.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking or frost with colored frosting after baking.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream all together except chocolate chips.
Roll out in cookie dish, pressing firmly.
Melt
chocolate
chips and pour on top. Cut into small squares
after
set.
You may place in freezer for 20 to 30
minutes
to
harden faster.
Tastes just like Reese's peanut butter cups!

title: potatoes ala "adair county"
directions: Prepare a double layer of aluminum foil sprayed with Pam. Slice potatoes.
Place on foil. Add margarine, parsley, garlic, pepper and salt.
Wrap foil by crimping the sides together.
Place on gas grill, upper rack, for approximately 35 minutes.
Open and serve!

title: vegetable pie
directions: Mix all vegetables in a 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pour mixture of eggs, milk, biscuit mix, salt and pepper over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up Danish or cinnamon buns and place in baking dish.
Mix eggs, vanilla, milk and sugar.
Pour 1/2 over Danish.
Put bread on top.
Pour remaining liquid on top of bread.
Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour or until firm and brown on top.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted butter.
Place pineapple rings (or crushed) on bottom of pan on top of butter and brown sugar.

title: festive ball o'cheese
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in a large Mixmaster bowl.
Beat with mixer until well mixed.
Grate Colby cheese and add to cream cheese mixture, mixing well.
Mold into a ball.
Decorate with paprika and chopped almonds or any other nuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and add to sauerkraut.
Cover bowl tightly and chill in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour together. In boiler, place the margarine, shortening, water and cocoa and bring to a boil. Pour this hot mixture over the sugar and flour and blend well. Add the buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and salt. Mix well. (Batter will be thin.) Pour into 11 x 16 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes only.

title: georgeann's seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta and the peas as per the package directions.
In a big salad bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Chill, if desired.
The dressing that we like to use is Jeffrey's Salad Dressing.
Toss well and serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a 5 quart Dutch oven, melt 1/4 cup margarine over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken bar-b-q
directions: Beat egg and add all remaining ingredients except the chicken.
Place the chicken parts in a deep bowl and marinate for 2 to 3 hours.
Put marinated chicken on grill and turn on occasionally and brush chicken with marinate frequently.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip cream, sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream cheese in separate bowl, then add to cream.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Melt butter; let cool.
Add eggs.
Mix together vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Add mixed sugar and flour a little at a time.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Bring barley to a boil in 3 cups of water.
Simmer 30 minutes. Drain.
Saute veggies in margarine in soup pot.
Add broth, bouillon, barley and Worcestershire sauce; cook until carrot is done.
Bring to a boil and add reserved cup of broth, mixed with cornstarch.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Season.

title: crusty peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Set aside until syrup forms. Bring peach mixture to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter, stirring until butter melts.

title: dorothy's tostitos dip
directions: Use 10-inch round tray.
Layer soft cream cheese, then spread salsa sauce on top of cheese.
Top layer with taco cheese.
Serve with tortilla or Tostitos chips.

title: tuna bake cheese swirls
directions: Cook pepper and onion in hot fat until golden; add salt and flour.
Blend.
Add soup and milk.
Cook until sauce is thick, stirring constantly.
Add flaked tuna and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into greased 10 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish and top with cheese swirls.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together well.
Pour half of batter into pan with apples and nuts; spread over top.
Pour rest of batter over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Heat to boiling water, 2 sticks of butter and 4 tablespoons of cocoa, then add and blend in well the flour, sugar, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add eggs and whole milk.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sylvia's oriental burgers
directions: Mix ingredients as you would meat loaf.
Mold into hamburger patties.
Grill and enjoy on buns.
Exotically different and delicious!

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Grind cabbage.
Chop onions and peppers. Mix raw vegetables and salt.
Add half of vinegar and bring to a boil.
Mix sugar, seasonings and flour together.
Add remaining vinegar.
Stir until smooth.
Cook until thickened.
Add to vegetables and cook for 30 minutes or until tender.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: hawaiian pickled onions
directions: You will need 1 quart jar with lid.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; tear into small pieces.
Fix dressing according to box.
Put on bottom of baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top of stuffing.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix 1 can of soup with milk.
Pour over noodles and mix.
Pour noodles on top of chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Cut margarine into flour; add milk.
Stir to remove lumps. This crust topping will be thin.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Boil sugar and syrup together for about 2 minutes.
Pour slowly over slightly beaten eggs, stirring vigorously.
Add butter or margarine, vanilla and nut meats.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick tuna melts
directions: Drain tuna and mix with soup and diced onion.
Separate tops and bottoms of rolls and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon mixture onto rolls and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine milk and chocolate morsels in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate melts.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into mugs.
Sprinkle evenly with marshmallows.
Makes 4 cups.

title: lime party salad
directions: In top of double boiler, melt marshmallow in milk.
Pour hot mixture over lime jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture and stir
until dissolved. Add crushed pineapple. Chill until mixture begins to thicken a little. Then add mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Serves about 12 people.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Place in loaf pan.

title: mrs. geary's french bread - 1952
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
While yeast softens, sift flour, sugar and salt together into a large bowl. Stir in the dissolved yeast. Add just enough of the second cup of water to hold dough together.
Mix until you have a soft, rather sticky dough.
Cover with a clean cloth and set bowl in a warm spot.
Let rise until double in size. This takes 2 to 4 hours depending on warmth of your kitchen.
When dough is high and spongy, punch it down with your fist and give it a good sound beating with your hand.
Divide bread dough into 2 parts and place each in a greased round baking dish.
Cover and let rise again until it reaches top of bowl. At this point, start your oven at 400°.
Brush top of bread with melted butter and bake 1 hour. Bread is finished when you tap the top and it sounds hollow.

title: betty's lean brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar and stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Add egg substitute and stir.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 25 minutes or until edges pull away from pan.
Cool in pan; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: cajun roast
directions: Preparation:
Tenderize the roast, using a fork (poking the heck out of it on both sides!).
Generously apply Tabasco sauce, ground black pepper and salt.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Place roast in roaster and smother with minced garlic and chopped onion. (Should cover meat completely.)
Cover tightly with foil and cook an hour per every pound of meat.
Serve in its own au jus gravy over your favorite rice.
Delicious!

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Melt butter in 5-quart pan over medium-high heat.

Add onion and cumin, stirring often, until onion is soft (about 10 minutes). Blend 1 to 2 tablespoons of the broth with cornstarch and pour into pan with remaining broth, corn, bell pepper and 1/4 cup salsa. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turn pink (3 to 5 minutes).
Ladle soup into 4 bowls.
Offer cheese and remaining salsa at the table.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pan.
Mix together sugar and 1 tablespoon flour, cinnamon and chopped nuts. Coat apples with this mixture and place in a baking dish.
Mix together oats, 3/4 cup flour, brown sugar and butter.
Pat on apple mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Bring a pot of water to boil and cook noodles for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Run cool water over noodles to prevent sticking.
Place the noodles in a bowl; chop the vegetables and place them in the bowl.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Pour Zesty italian dressing over the salad.
Mix the ingredients to coat.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in olive oil.
Prepare noodles.
Brown hamburger meat.
While noodles and hamburger are cooking, combine soups, corn and sour cream together.
Drain noodles and meat.
Add all ingredients in large bowl and stir well.
Put in 3 to 4 liter casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes with cover. Sprinkle butter and bread crumbs on top and bake 10 minutes without cover.
Serves 6.
Serve with jello and whole wheat rolls.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to apples and add vanilla, nuts, eggs and oil; mix together.
Bake in long or round pan, floured and oiled for 1 hour at 325°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender, then add to bowl.
Form mixture into small balls.
Brown and bake 1 hour at 350° in covered bowl.
Add drippings and water.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, add vanilla and oil; blend well.
Add zucchini, gradually add the dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fruity bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients (except apples and raisins).
Soak bread for 3 or 4 hours in this mixture.
Add apples and raisins and mix together.
Spray baking dish with vegetable spray.
Add mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese with Bisquick mix.
Add crumbled, uncooked sausage and mix well.
Add 1 tablespoon water if necessary to mix.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Bring water to a boil over moderate heat in medium size pan. Slowly add jello mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.
Arrange berries in pie shell and pour filling over berries. Chill at least 1 hour. Top with Cool Whip.
Real good!

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar with 1/2 of beer. Add rest of beer. Put into greased loaf pan. Bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cowboy bean casserole
directions: Brown ham in butter; combine garlic, beans, ham, mustard and seasonings.
Pour into a greased baking dish; top with onion slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add marshmallow, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter; beat egg, lemon rind and vanilla. Mix sifted flour and baking powder; slowly mix ingredients.
Roll dough on a board.
Cut into shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Drain oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer until desired thickness, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tangy coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage very fine or use a food processor.
Cut pepper crosswise into thin rings.
Cut onion crosswise in thin slices and separate into rings.
Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise and chill.

title: deli cheese balls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add corned beef.
Form into balls and roll in chopped nuts or in chopped olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: couscous coquettes
directions: Cook couscous in skillet over medium heat until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add water, raisins and salt.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and let stand 5 to 10 minutes, covered.
In small pan, cook onion and garlic in the olive oil; add carrots and celery and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
In large bowl, beat eggs, stir in couscous, carrot mix, bread crumbs, parsley or mint. Shape into 1/3 cup measure and unmold on baking sheet.
Flatten, cover and chill at least an hour (up to 24 hours).
They hold shape better when chilled longer.
Cook in a little oil 5 to 7 minutes until crispy and brown.

title: chinese sauce for chicken wings
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Cook in hot oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 400° until crisp.
(A big crowd pleaser.)

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange peaches over top of batter.
Combine cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon over peaches.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Sprinkle over top.

title: crepes(palacinky)
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs and salt.
Mix well using a whisk.
Add a little flour, then a little milk.
Stir; repeat until all flour and milk are added.
Mix until smooth.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease bottom of small skillet. Heat pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tablespoons batter.
Swirl pan so batter spreads evenly.
Cook crepes until golden brown.
Gently flip and cook other side just a few seconds. "You can spread with jam, roll up and sprinkle with powdered sugar."

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw and drain shrimp.
Blot excess moisture and chill.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Pour into serving dish and chill.
Just before serving, pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese mixture, top with shrimp.
Serve with tortillas chips for dipping.

title: golden wassail
directions: Mix juices in at least 20-cup electric percolator.
Place rest of ingredients in basket.
Perk as for coffee.
Serve hot.
Yield: Twenty 1/2-cup servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs with melted margarine.
Spread half of the crumb mixture over bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together cabbage and onion; spread over crumbs.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle dish with remaining crumbs.
Cover crumbs with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread pudding
directions: Cube bread into medium chunks.
Combine all ingredients, except milk.
Add bread chunks.
Stir in enough milk to make thick batter.
Bake at 250° in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan for about 3 to 4 hours.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Bring these ingredients to a boil.
Pour this mixture over coated biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn pan upside down immediately after removing from oven to avoid sticking.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add celery and other vegetables.
Last 1/2 hour, add 1/4 cup Minute rice.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Makes almost full slow cooker.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients in a separate bowl. Mix both dry and wet ingredients together.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper.
Cook until tender. Stir in seasoning mix, tomatoes and noodles.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat cheese, vanilla and sugar together.
Add whip cream; mix well.
Add berries of any kind; mix well.
Pour into crust and freeze, approximately 2 hours.

title: cowboy sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Will fill 8 buns.

title: stephanie's pecan crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Sift flour and add to mixture.
Then put in vanilla and cream; add nuts.
Roll in small pieces; shape into crescents.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Wait 2 minutes and while still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Sift sugar.
Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Add everything else except for chips and paraffin.
Chill overnight.
Form balls and chill again.
Melt chips and paraffin over low heat.
Use a toothpick to drop each ball and coat.
Place on waxed paper.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers, bread, whatever.

title: coconut oatmeal pie(convection oven recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans in large bowl.
Add pecans; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Place on broiling trivet.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes; then bake 15 minutes on low mix, 375° or until set.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute the garlic, beans, broccoli, zucchini, tomatoes, thyme, salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn and mix.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
(This dries the syrup on the corn so it will separate.) 250° may be too hot in some ovens, so 225° or 200° might be sufficient.

title: onion casserole
directions: Put in greased casserole dish.
Arrange onions.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with mayonnaise and serve hot.

title: broccoli peanut salad
directions: In bowl, thin mayonnaise with dressing.
Add remaining ingredients except peanuts.
Toss to coat with dressing.
Add nuts before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tofu stir-fry
directions: Drain and cut tofu into cubes.
Fry tofu in vegetable oil at 400° until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain oil.
Add can of whole tomatoes.
Use spatula to cut up tomatoes while allowing to simmer with tofu.
Next, cut up vegetables and add to frying pan with tofu and tomatoes.
Stir, then add on corn.
Allow ingredients to simmer for 20 minutes with occasional stirring. During this time, you may prepare rice for a complete meal.

title: delicious teriyaki steak
directions: Mix together garlic powder, onion powder, sugar, soy sauce, diced onion and pepper.
Marinate meat in mixture for 2 hours. Stir-fry steak and set aside.
Stir-fry vegetables.
Add 1 cup beef broth and steak.
Mix cornstarch with marinade sauce and add to vegetable and steak mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in water in large soup pot.
Bring to boil and simmer.
Add all the rest of the ingredients; cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Separately boil noodles, then add to the soup at the end.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve syrup.
Prepare jello as directed on box, using syrup as part of water.
Add strawberries to jello. When jello is almost firm, add ice cream, a little at a time, mixing with electric mixer.
Whip cream and fold into mixture. Place in freezer and serve when frozen.

title: snowy coconut treats(for children)
directions: Put margarine in bowl; stir in sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Spread mixture on graham crackers.
May be put under broiler for a minute to brown.

title: 10 minute szechuan chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Toss in cornstarch.
Heat oil and add chicken and garlic.
Stir-fry until browned.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and water.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add green onions and cayenne and heat 2 minutes.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings at 221 calories each.

title: summer cooler
directions: I discovered this while boating last summer.
Carefully choose different colored fruits and cut them into bite-size bits.
I use kiwi, strawberries, cantaloupe, grapes and raisins.
Mix however much yogurt you desire with the fruit.
It is refreshing and nutritional.
I like to use lemon yogurt.

title: my special rice
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion until soft.
Add parsley and rice.
Stir well and heat covered on low.
Serves 3.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Place in serving dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.

title: party rolls
directions: Mix mayonnaise and brown mustard.
Slice rolls and spread mayonnaise mixture and mustard mixture on both sides.
Put a layer of meat and a layer of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix broth and chicken soup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk, butter and pepper to form batter. Spoon over chicken. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine cornbread stuffing and bread crumbs in large bowl. Pour turkey juice over crumbs to soften.
Add chopped celery, chopped onion, cream of chicken soup, sliced eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Do not get mixture too soggy.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares when cool or dip with spoon while warm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend together first 2 ingredients and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add remaining 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in sour cream.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until firm.
Turn off oven.
Leave door slightly ajar and allow cheesecake to remain in oven for 1 hour. Cool in pan.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Top with your choice of pie filling (cherry, blueberry, etc.).

title: summer casserole(bushels of zucchini?  a delicious way to use some.)
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
For a larger family or a larger crop, add more zucchini.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts; skin them.
Lay ham and cheese on one side and fold other side over.
Hold together with wooden toothpick.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs and flour.
Brown in melted butter in skillet.
Place chicken in baking dish in oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Make white sauce with Cheddar cheese; pour over to serve.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Using a hand mixer, thoroughly mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread mixture evenly over large, round, flat serving platter.
Evenly layer the rest of the ingredients in the following order:
salsa, green pepper, tomato, lettuce and Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: violet's cherry crisp "dump cake"
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix all together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each
foil liner muffin cup.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes in 325°
oven.
Top with Comstock cherries or leave plain.

title: mama's hot peppers
directions: Cut peppers into rings or desired pieces.
Place peppers in large container and stir in salt.
Allow to sit overnight in cool place.
Next day, thoroughly rinse off salt.
Stir in oil, garlic and oregano.
Cold pack 1/4 to 1/2 inch from top of jar for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Ranch dressing according to package.
Wash broccoli and cauliflower. Break both into bite size pieces. Cut carrots into small pieces.
Toss all with dressing mix.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: loyd's chicken(serves 8)
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
It is good served with rice.

title: vege-chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce cups.
Serves 6.

title: guacamole
directions: Blend until smooth.
Serve as spread or topping.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: samuel and michael's beenie weenie chili macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni per instructions on box.
Empty 1 can of chili into macaroni when cooked.
Slice wieners into mixture and cook until all ingredients are heated.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown chicken; remove from pan.
Add the onion, garlic and green pepper; cook until tender.
Return chicken to pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour, until the chicken is tender.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Heat grease; add onion and saute.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, catsup, chili powder, garlic salt and pork and beans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork with apples and apple cider
directions: Place pork slices between plastic wrap.
Pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add apples and sugar to skillet and saute until brown (6 minutes).
Set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in another heavy skillet over high heat.
Season pork with salt and pepper.
Add pork and saute until just cooked through.
Transfer to plate and keep warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken bite size (cooked).
Fry bacon; drain and reserve 2 tablespoons of grease.
Brown in grease.
Add bacon, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook the cake mix as directed and cool. Crumble a layer of cooled cake in a
punch bowl.
Mix the vanilla pudding as directed.
Spread pudding over crumbled cake.
Spread the pineapple with juice over the pudding. Add another layer of crumbled cake. Spread the pie filling over cake.
Layer the Cool Whip over top. Add the nuts over top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars, then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour in small amounts until all is added.
Shape into 1-inch balls; press down with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool on rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: batterbread (spoon bread)
directions: Place cornmeal, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan and add boiling water.
Add milk, beaten eggs and baking powder.
Melt butter in casserole and swish to coat container.
Add butter to saucepan.
Cook slowly on top of stove.
When it thickens, put in casserole and bake at 400° to 425° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: au gratin potato bake
directions: Remove skins from potatoes; shred potatoes into bowl, using medium blade or shredder.
Add cheese.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup melted butter in saucepan or until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch 3-quart baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes, drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
