Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Garnish with pimento and parsley.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk in saucepan over high heat to soft ball stage. Pour over other ingredients in bowl (large) and mix with mixer until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into cookie sheet (buttered).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.
Serve with fruit.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into two well-greased 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Turn out cake. While cake is cooling, make the icing.

title: easy apricot squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except the jam.
Pat 3/4 of the dough on bottom of pan.
Spread with jam.
Sprinkle rest of dough on top for crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in gumdrops and mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Let Grape-Nuts stand in milk for 5 minutes. Add the remaining beaten ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of the crumbs. Press remaining crumbs onto bottom and 2-inches up the sides of a generously buttered 10-inch spring-form pan.
Stir cream cheese to soften.
Beat until fluffy.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare Stove Top dressing according to package directions. Combine the soup and milk and set aside. Place a heaping tablespoonful of dressing on each chicken breast and then roll the breast up. Spray oven dish with nonstick spray. Place the chicken breast open side down in the pan. Pour milk and soup over the top. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin tin greased with Pam. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 45 muffins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour crushed pineapple in bottom of cake pan.
Pour peach pie filling over top of crushed pineapple.
Pour dry cake mix over peach pie filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushroom pieces in butter or margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain; add to onion mixture.
Add mushroom soup.
Melt cheese in double boiler or microwave; add to mixture.
Serves 12.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make roux with butter and flour.
Add milk and chicken broth; cook until thick.
Add potatoes.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Garnish with chives, crumbled bacon and Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet and then drain.
Stir in the taco sauce and beans and 1 cup of the cheese.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Dip with your favorite chips. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: basic blue crab stuffing
directions: Cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
May use mayonnaise and milk if too dry.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium-high heat. Drain fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Yields about 25 servings.
Can make up full recipe and freeze into portions before they are baked for smaller servings.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pare a strip of skin about 1/2-inch wide around center of each potato.
Place in medium saucepan.
Add boiling water to measure 2 inches and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling; boil gently covered, 20 minutes or just until potatoes are tender.
Drain; return to heat several minutes to dry out. Add butter, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the parsley; toss gently to coat well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.	Bring
margarine, oil and cocoa to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add to flour and sugar mixture.
Then add baking powder, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon to mixture.

title: mocha balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except coconut.
Roll into one inch
balls
and
roll
in coconut.
Keep hands wet while rolling. Store at least two days before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut meat into strips.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat; cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 10 minutes for sirloin.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering while meat simmers.
Cook instant rice as directed on package for 4 to 6 servings.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into eighths and place on meat mixture.
Cover; cook over low heat just until tomatoes are heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes in an 8 to 10-inch black skillet or a 9-inch glass pie pan, greased.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and roll in cracker crumbs or cereal.
Make patties and brown in oil.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain strawberries, pineapple and oranges.
Mix together in a large bowl.
Chill before serving.
If salad is to be chilled overnight, it is best to add the bananas just before serving. Serves 6 to 8.
Good to serve with breakfast casserole.

title: reduced calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except crust in a microwave-safe bowl. Using an electric mixer, beat until smooth.
Microwave, uncovered, for 5 minutes at High, stirring often.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Microwave for 12 to 15 minutes at Medium (50%) or until center is almost set, but looks slightly moist.
Rotate pan once if necessary for even cooking.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise (use judgement on how much).
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9 baking dish, melt margarine. Remove from heat. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine. Pour milk evenly over the crumbs; top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Press down gently. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: meat roll ups
directions: Add stuffing mixture to meat and roll up.
Place in pan, seam side down.
Pour soup over top of meat and stuffing rolls and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 5 x 12-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown together the ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain off fat.
Cool mixture.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine corn flakes and butter (margarine may be used). Put into 9 x 12 inch casserole pan-reserve some crumbs for topping. Mix cabbage, onion, chestnuts and add on top of crumbs. Mix lst ingredients and pour over the cabbage mixture.
Grate cheese and put on top.
Add reserved corn flakes.
Bake i n 350 oven for 45 minutes.

title: french bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Put water in a large bowl.
Sprinkle on yeast and let stand, stirring once or twice until it dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, oil and salt.
Beat in 2 cups of flour.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft, not too sticky, dough.
Work dough with hands until slightly elastic, 3 minutes.
(In this recipe, it is not necessary to turn dough out and knead on a board.)
Cover dough with dish towel and let it rest 15 minutes.
Then transfer dough to a clean bowl and repeat procedure 3 more times.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together and add this to butter mixture.
Add pecans and shape into balls. Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt, thyme, cumin and chili powder and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add red pepper to taste.
Cover with water and simmer for one hour.
Add red food coloring to add color if desired.

title: no fat potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cover with Italian dressing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 medium loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
You can make 1 large loaf and bake for 1 hour.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling rest of freezer with milk.
Freeze.

title: covey smith's first grade cookbook peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugars.	Add
egg,
vanilla
and peanut butter; beat well.	Mix in dry ingredients.
Shape into small balls and flatten.	Bake until brown.

title: saucy hot dogs
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar well. Add the remaining wet ingredients. Blend together until smooth.
Place hot dogs in a shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce evenly over hot dogs.
Bake in oven at 350° until sauce thickens (15 to 20 minutes) or microwave on High until sauce thickens (3 to 6 minutes). Serve on hot dog rolls with finely chopped onions.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together.
Put all ingredients into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash the potatoes.
Blend in rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dutch man's delight
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and dip in powdered sugar.

title: home fries
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise in strips.
Cover with water. Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Put dry mixes in a paper bag.
Remove potatoes from water.
Drop potatoes in bag and shake. Deep fry in hot grease.

title: red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first three ingredients into soft dough. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until brown at 375°.
Mix last three ingredients and brush on hot biscuits.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Stir to blend.
Add shrimp and stir to coat.
Let stand until ready to cook.

title: quick green bean dish
directions: Saute onion and bacon.
Add green beans and tomato sauce. Stir in brown sugar.
Heat and serve.
Good with beef dishes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and melted margarine; press firmly on bottom and side of 8 or 9-inch pie pan. Chill.

title: chicken breasts with tarragon
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper; dredge with flour.
Reserve remaining flour.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Transfer to warm platter. Add shallots and saute briefly.
Add wine.
Cook on high until nearly evaporated, scraping brown particles loose.
Add reserved flour and stir to make a thick paste.
Sprinkle with tarragon and stir in chicken broth.
Add chicken, cover and cook until tender, about 25 minutes.
Transfer chicken to platter and keep hot.
Add remaining batter and cream to skillet.
Heat and stir.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix the flour and baking soda together very well. Then beat the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla separate of the flour and the baking soda.
Beat them well. Add nutmeg and sour cream with everything and mix it all together.

title: aunt mae's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all except vanilla together and cook until thick. Add vanilla. Pour into cooked shell. Beat egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Put on top and cook until brown at 250°.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil and reduce heat slightly.
Continue cooking about 1/2 hour.
Add liquid to keep from sticking if necessary.
It should be slightly soupy but more like stew.
Serve with crackers or bread and a relish tray of pickles, carrot sticks, etc.

title: baked carrots
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; add onions.
Cook slowly until soft.
Add carrots, sugar and salt; add water.
Bake at 350° until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer as follows:
ground beef and frozen peas.
Cover with chicken soup mixed with 1/2 cup milk.
Layer Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly and hamburger is done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: feather light pie crust
directions: Have shortening at room temperature.
Cut into flour and salt. Add egg and vinegar.
Add cold water.
Chill if you wish.
Never stretch the crust when fitting in the pan.

title: red hot ketchup
directions: Combine all ingredients into sauce pan. Cook until thick. Pour in clean jars.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in pie shell.
Dab with butter or oleo.
Top with other pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tuna-cheese pie
directions: Beat Bisquick, milk, salt, pepper and eggs together for 1 minute; set aside.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook onions and oleo over low heat for 5 minutes.
Dump into baking dish with 1 cup of cheese, tuna and Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and 1 cup cheese. Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press crescent rolls into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with McCormick's Salad Supreme.

title: lemon-lime refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water; set aside at room temperature. Mix and bake cake as directed in a 9x13x2 pan. Cool cake 20-25 minutes. Poke deep holes through top of warm cake (still in pan) with meat fork or toothpick; space holes about one inch apart. With a cup, slowly pour gelatin mixture into holes. Refrigerate cake while preparing topping.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and flavorings thoroughly. Gradually add sugar, taking time to thoroughly cream sugar into butter mixture; add eggs, one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream and milk. At this point, beat only enough until the ingredients are well blended. Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Pour batter into pan. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 - 2 hours or until test done. Allow to stand in pan about 10 minutes before turning out. Frost or glaze as desired.

title: john's favorite potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with a mixture of 2 cups of corn flake crumbs and 1/2 cup butter, melted.
Bake at 325° to 350°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat.
Add flour and blend well.
Pat into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix in egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Add to pan as second layer.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with apples until well coated.
Add to pan. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: mocha cheese cake
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese; add Eagle Brand milk and chocolate syrup.
In cup, dissolve coffee in hot water.
Add to Eagle Brand mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pan.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm. Serves 6.

title: texas breakfast
directions: Fry potatoes until tender.
Fry sausage while potatoes are cooking.
After potatoes and sausage are cooked, layer sausage over potatoes.
Pour beaten eggs over sausage and potato layer.
Cover and let cook.
When eggs are cooked, add green peppers on top of eggs.
Put cheese slices on top of green peppers.
Cover and let cheese melt.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix meat, salt, garlic powder, black pepper and 1/4 cup minced onion together.
Let set in fridge at least 2 hours.
Make meatballs.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and add remaining ingredients.
Don't add ginger ale until ready to serve.
Makes 10 gallons.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix together all except pecans and parsley. Shape into ball. Roll in pecans and parsley. Serve with onion crackers. Freezes well.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix well and spread over cake while cake is still hot and then heat under broiler until topping bubbles up.
Allow cake to cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry glazed pork loin roast
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow baking pan.
Roast uncovered in 325° oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours (allow about 30 to 35 minutes per pound).
Meanwhile, in bowl, combine pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Spoon cherry glaze over roast several times during last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Remove meat from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.
Heat remaining glaze and serve with roast.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix together soup and milk.
Place 1/2 of the potatoes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half the onions and half the soup mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Heat in microwave on High 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; mix well.
Add asparagus juice, making a paste.
Return to heat.
Add cream, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings (salt, pepper, paprika and red pepper).
Add cheese, chopped.
Stir until dissolved.
Add mushrooms.
Drain asparagus. Line bottom of casserole with 1 can asparagus.
Cover with cheese sauce and sliced boiled eggs.
Repeat and top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: two egg cake layers
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat real good. Place in 2 cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buttercream decorator icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening together. Add vanilla and salt. Beat in sugar, one cup at a time. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often to make sure sugar is well blended. Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy. Keep frosting covered in the refrigerator when not in use.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish, uncovered. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl and mix. Store airtight for 1 month. Makes about 1/3 cup.

title: spinach dip
directions: Place all ingredients in small bowl and mix well.
Serve with small pieces of Vienna bread as a dip.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Save egg whites for meringue.
Mix all except water.
Add the water last.
Cook on low heat or double boiler until thickened. Put in baked shell.
Make meringue.

title: chicken 'n green bean casserole
directions: *Or use 2 packages (9 ounces each) frozen cut green beans, cooked and drained.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Use lasagna pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook 1 cup of rice and set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla or lemon flavoring and milk together.
Add to rice.
Cook to 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour, until brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed of hand electric mixer until well blended and smooth.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, until center is almost set. Cool.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Heat oil (2 to 3-inches) in deep-fat fryer or heavy kettle to 375°.
Beat 1 1/2 cups of the flour and the remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto well-floured cloth-covered board; roll around lightly to coat with flour.
Roll gently 3/8-inch thick.

title: sassy cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix
according to package directions substituting milk for water.
Bake in
layers.
Cool layers and split each. Mix coconut, sugar
and
sour
cream
thoroughly.
Place filling on top of each layer reserving approximately 3/4 cup to mix with Cool Whip.
Frost top
and
sides
with Cool Whip mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Best when made a day ahead.

title: beef roast
directions: Wash meat and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and tenderizer.
Place in roaster and add water.
Cover and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel-strawberry dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar and pretzels.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry eclair
directions: Stir over low heat about 1 minute until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat and add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
This is like a cream puff pastry.
Spoon into a greased pizza pan (12-inch or larger) almost to the edge to form a ring. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Slice in half through middle.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Scald milk and slowly add to beaten eggs seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook macaroni according to instructions.
Add cheese to hot macaroni.
Then add egg mixture to this.
Put in greased casserole and set this in a pan of warm water.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes to completely dissolve.
Pour boiling water over shortening and salt in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm; stir in yeast, then add half of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour and again beat until smooth.
On floured board, divide dough in half and pat into rounds or oblong shapes, having edges slightly thicker to keep filling from running over during baking.
Place on greased pizza pan or cookie sheet and let rise until double in height.

title: pineapple casserole(salad or dessert)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add cheese to pineapple and stir.

title: bean salad
directions: *Any of these may be used also.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, boiling water, Coke, cheese and rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: tomato special
directions: Take raw hamburg.
Mess up in flat casserole dish.
Slice up potatoes (with or without skins).
Mix up in raw hamburg.
Last, add tomato soup.
Mix everything well.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: continental butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and confectioner sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift together regular flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough on floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in preheated oven.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Mix soup and milk.
Combine 1/2 of the soup mixture, the vegetables, the croutons and half the onions and pepper.
Place in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour remaining soup mixture over casserole.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, about 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Cool; mix all ingredients together and serve cold.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: basic fruit pie filling
directions: Simmer
apples
or pears until tender.
Add flavors and thickening.
For
peach or berry just combine juice and thickener. Stir
until
thick.
Add
fruit.
If using cooked juicy fruit, add
no juice, only flavors and thickening.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and eggs, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: oriental chicken and pasta salad
directions: In 6-quart or 8-quart saucepan, fill 3/4 with cold water or pinch of salt.
Cover until boil; cook spaghetti until soft.
Drain and set aside.
Saute oil, garlic and crushed red pepper for 1 minute.
Add carrots, celery, green onion, green pepper and red pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add ginger, sugar, soy sauce and chicken and mix well.
Cook for 2 more minutes.
Add bean sprouts. Remove from heat.
Add spaghetti to above.
Place in suitable covered container in refrigerator until well chilled, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour yeast into water and let stand 5 minutes.
Scald milk; add sugar and salt.
Let cool.
When lukewarm, add to yeast; add 1/2 flour and potatoes.
Beat until smooth.
Add shortening and rest of flour to make soft dough.
May need to knead a few minutes.
Let set in warm place until double in size.
Knead dough and refrigerate; cover with wax paper or plastic bag.
Two hours before needed, shape in rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out of oven and brush with butter.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cook as directed on box; top with apple jelly, then top with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb meringue dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat in 9-inch square pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: baked halibut or flounder
directions: Steam spinach until wilted, set aside.
Saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine.
Set aside.
Put spinach in Pyrex dish and top with mushrooms and garlic.
Place flounder on top of spinach and mushrooms.
Season with parsley, basil, tarragon and top with margarine.
Bake in moderate oven until fish flakes and is opaque. Serve with French rolls and herbed butter.

title: slushy fruit
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add orange juice and lemon juice. stir in all fruit.
Freeze 24 hours Thaw halfway to serve.

title: flan(a spanish custard)
directions: Cook sugar and water until light brown.
Pour immediately into pan which is at least 2 inches deep and 8 inches wide.
Cool. Blend flan ingredients in blender or food processor until no lumps.
Pour into cooled flan pan.
Put this into a larger pan with water in it about halfway up on smaller flan pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and unmold or serve from pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese, in 4-quart pressure cooker.
Cook 12 minutes at 15 pounds pressure. Reduce pressure quickly under cold running water.
Serve over cooked spaghetti. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello.
Cool and add sliced peaches.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shells.

title: szechwan peanut chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce, garlic and ginger; set aside 10 minutes.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken mixture in oil until no longer pink, about 3 minutes.
Add red pepper, picante sauce and peanut butter.
Cook and stir 4 minutes.
Add green onions; heat through.

title: cookie pie
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour mixture into unbaked shell.
Bake below oven center at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until top is golden brown and toothpick when inserted into center, comes out clean.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: eggplant en casserole
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick; remove skin and cut into dice to make about 5 cups of dice.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in a skillet and saute the eggplant slowly for about 5 minutes.
Place in a buttered casserole with alternate layers of sliced onions, diced tomatoes and grated cheese, saving 1/4 cup cheese for top; season each layer.
Top with crumbs which have been mixed with remaining cheese and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) until vegetables are tender and surface is nicely browned, about 35 minutes.
Makes 5 generous servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour and spices together add to wet mixture.
Add prunes and mix well.
Pour into well greased and floured 9 x 13 pan and bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: In a large pot, mix Karo syrup and sugar.
Heat to boiling. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch together.
Spread over top of cookies.
When topping has set, cut into bars.

title: ice cream balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use softened ice cream and shape into balls.
Roll ice cream into mixture.
Wrap into foil and refreeze.
To serve, pour hot fudge over each serving.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda by hand well.
Add margarine, sugar, egg and buttermilk and mix well.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix well. Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake one hour.
Cool on rack.

title: candy bar delight
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 with ice cream sandwiches.
Spread Cool Whip over sandwiches.
Crush candy bars and spread over Cool Whip. Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Stir together; pour into muffin tins (lightly greased).
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with chopped onion and green pepper.
Cook and drain noodles in a 2 or 3-quart pan.
In a casserole dish, add meat mixture, soups and cooked noodles.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can put cheese on top.

title: jambalaya
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook, covered, 5 to 10 minutes or
until liquid is absorbed. Makes 6 servings.

title: teriyaki jerky
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate meat in mixture for approximately 1 hour.
Put in electric smoker for 8 hours.

title: old fashioned butter rolls
directions: Makes 2 rolls in pan.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan 2 cups water, 1 cup milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix and set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine the Bisquick; mix as for biscuits on box ingredients.
Halve the dough and roll out in a rectangle; sprinkle with about 3/4 cup sugar.
Roll up from long side.
Repeat with remainder of dough.
Place in pan with milk mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on tops of rolls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until brown.

title: black-eyed pea dip(servings:  4)
directions: Combine all ingredients except peas and bring to a melting simmer.
Add peas and serve with chips or crackers.

title: triple batch beef roast
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add beef (1/4 at a time).
Cook and stir until beef is browned.
Remove beef from pan, season with salt and pepper and set aside.
Cook garlic and onions in pan until lightly browned.
Pour off drippings; return beef to pan.
Add water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until beef is tender.
Skim off fat. Place about 2 cups of beef mixture into each of 3 (1-quart) freezer containers.
Cover tightly and freeze.
Use in Beef Stew, Quick and Easy Beef Barley Soup and 20 Minute Beef Chili.
Or, use your imagination!
Very good!

title: k f c "baked" chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together and put in plastic bag.
Wash chicken.
While wet, place in bag with dry mixture.
Coat well and place on greased baking pan.
Pour melted butter or margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Baste with juices every 15 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, Karo and salt in 2-quart glass microwave-safe dish.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more on High.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more on High.
Stir in butter until melted, cook 2 minutes and 25 seconds more.
Add soda and stir gently and quickly.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet; cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: ryan's breakfast migas
directions: Mix eggs (as many as you need) as if they are scrambled; salt and pepper.
Heat Crisco oil (enough to cover chips) and cut or tear tortillas (I usually cut them into 8 pieces) and cook them in oil until crisp.
Slowly add eggs and mix.
When eggs are almost cooked, add as much cheese and salsa as you like.

title: hot dog potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin. Cut hot dogs about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange potatoes and hot dogs in alternate layers in greased baking dish or casserole, beginning and ending with potatoes.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Blend in flour.
Add milk and cut up cheese.
Stir over low heat until sauce boils and cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes and hot dogs, topped with extra cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a pan, add water to cover and simmer until tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly, peel potatoes and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces, place potatoes in a bowl and set aside.
Combine brown sugar, margarine and orange.
Cook over medium heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture over potatoes, toss gently.
May heat more in microwave just before serving.
Yields 8 servings.
Fat:
0.2 grams.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Use as dessert or salad.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with wheat crackers and corn chips.

title: chinese pepper chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, soy sauce, garlic, ginger root and cornstarch.
Toss chicken in sauce to coat and marinate 30 minutes.
In a wok heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil and cook peppers and celery over high heat, stirring frequently until softened.
Add green onions and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove vegetables from wok.
Drain chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Add chicken to wok and stir-fry until chicken is done, about 3 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a small bowl.
Add to chicken with vegetables; simmer 3 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 20 g, fat 9 g, calories 186.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except croutons, in pot.
Cook over low heat 4 to 6 hours or over high heat 2 hours, stirring frequently. Serve in warm bowls.
Top each with croutons.
Good with or without beer.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook onions, celery and oil in Dutch oven or large saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add meat, water, soy sauce and molasses and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Heat and stir in the cornstarch blended with a little cool water.
Cook until thickened and serve over chow mein noodles.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° after mixing together.
May be assembled the night before and refrigerated.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put all of the ingredients in a crock-pot and simmer.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Bring pie filling, water and sugar to a boil.
Let boil for 1 minute. Empty Jell-O into a large bowl. Pour hot mixture over Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and pecans. Add the Coke last.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam. Chill overnight.

title: sandy's soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add other ingredients.
Warm and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese with ham
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
In saucepan, cook onion and ham in butter until tender.
Butter a casserole dish and mix macaroni and salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion and ham.
Top with shredded cheese and bake in 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.
This is also good without the ham.

title: cavatini casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Cook noodles.
Mix meat and noodles together.
Mix spaghetti sauce and soup together; pour over meat and noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into a sprayed casserole dish. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes to let cheese brown slightly.
Serves 10.

title: betty's beef stew
directions: In 4 or 5-quart pan, heat oil.
Add onion and cook over medium heat (1 to 2 minutes).
Add beef and stir to combine.
Cook until beef is brown (about 15 minutes).
Stir frequently.

title: prairie fire dip
directions: Put beans through a sieve.
Mix all ingredients and heat over hot water until cheese is melted.
Serve hot from chafing dish with fried tortillas or potato chips.

title: swiss chard casserole
directions: Trim ribs from chard (or stems from spinach); wash well and cook in a large pan with 1 teaspoon salt and 2 tablespoons water (no water for spinach) until leaves have greatly reduced in bulk and are tender, 5 to 7 minutes for chard, less for spinach.
Drain well in a colander, pressing out water and chop greens finely.
In large bowl, mix greens with eggs, butter, green onion, cheese and cottage cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until set.
Serves 6 to 8.
May be made ahead and refrigerated, but allow a little extra cooking time.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 pie shells.
Add topping to all of these.

title: chocolate nut icing
directions: Bring margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and frost your favorite cake.

title: dump cake(oldie, but goodie)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof baking dish, spread cherry pie filling.
Next, spread pineapple and juice, then sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Slice and spread margarine.
Sprinkle on coconut, then pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until brown on top. Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt well.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly.
In small bowl mix egg, vinegar and 1/2 cup of water. Combine with first mix until moistened.
Divide dough into 4 portions and wrap in plastic.
Chill between 1/2 and 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board.

title: vic's snickers cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box. Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Melt caramels, butter and milk together. Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture. Pour the remaining cake batter over the top of all. Bake for an additional 20 minutes at 250° and then 10 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned potato salad(over 50 years old)
directions: Use leftover mashed potatoes or cook as many potatoes as needed.
Mash the potatoes.
Add chopped onions.
Then add vinegar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large skillet, mix the filling as follows:
saute onion, celery and carrots.
Chop chicken breasts into 1-inch cubes.
Add to vegetables.
Continue to stir until chicken is cooked.
Add cream of chicken soup and Veg-All.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in 9-inch deep pie shell and add top crust.
Vent crust. Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbling. Let rest 10 minutes before slicing.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour with baking powder and add to creamed mixture. Roll out, cut and place on cookie sheet. Brush with egg white and decorate. Bake 5 plus minutes in 375° oven. Great for kids!

title: hamburger and noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Melt butter in skillet; add onion and celery cut up in small pieces.
Crumble hamburger in skillet on vegetables.
Add small amount of salt and pepper.
Stir until browned.
Add one can of mushroom soup and 1 can tomato soup. Heat mix with noodles.
Put in greased baking dish with grated cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and slice pears.
Put the pears through the fine blade of a food chopper or use your processor.
Combine pears, pineapple and sugar in a large kettle and bring to boil, stirring occasionally until the sugar has all dissolved.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, or until the mixture is thickened.
Stir frequently.
If you like a brighter, golden color, drop in a couple drops each of red and yellow food coloring.
Pour the honey into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
You may let them cool and pour melted paraffin over if you wish.

title: quick shrimp etouffee
directions: Salt and pepper shrimp and allow to set for at least 2 hours. In large saucepan, saute onion and green peppers in margarine until clear.
Add soups with only enough water to rinse out cans. Add tomato sauce.
Add shrimp and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Great with a salad and French bread.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Soften cream cheese and beat to remove lumps. Mix all together and season to taste with season salt, pepper, garlic powder and basil. Simmer 1 hour. If too thick, use V-8 to thin. Serve with Mozzarella cheese and croutons.

title: carrot-zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved. Add carrots and zucchini (shredded).
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour in greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and potato chips (crushed).
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: venison sauce(1788)
directions: Cover a large tongue with about two quarts of water.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar, 2 tablespoons sugar, a large clove garlic (chopped), a bay leaf and a teaspoon of cumin seed.
Boil until very tender. Allow to cool, then peel.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook onions, celery, green pepper and garlic until tender. Remove from pan.
Brown meat and pour fat off.
Add onion mixture, chili sauce, relish, brown sugar, vinegar, garlic, salt, pepper, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook at least 40 minutes.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage until brown and drain.
Grease large baking dish. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into dish.
Put in fridge overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve this with croissants, jams and jellies and fresh fruits.

title: caramel pecan cake
directions: Prepare cake.
Cool completely.
Beat together caramel ice cream topping and butter in a large mixing bowl until smooth. Gradually add powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans, beating until frosting is creamy and spreadable.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve. Let cake stand at room temperature for approximately 30 minutes for easier cutting.

title: chicken mandalay(no cholesterol)
directions: Shake in bag until chicken is coated.
Brown in 4 tablespoons olive oil until chicken is golden brown.

title: beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients except French fried onions.
Pour half the mixture into greased pan.
Top with 1/2 can onions.
Pour remaining macaroni mixture over onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix like meatloaf in bowl meat, salt and pepper, egg, ketchup, potatoes, milk and onion.
Put in pie plate after mixing and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cheese cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir to blend.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve in hollowed out round loaf of French bread, rye or pumpernickel; use hollowed out section to make bread cubes for dipping.
Great with fresh vegetables to dip too.
Enjoy!
Yields 6 servings.

title: homemade bread(this recipe is over 100 years old.)
directions: Add sugar, salt and oil or shortening to scalded milk.
Let milk cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Gradually stir in flour to milk.
Flour dough board and knead. Work dough approximately 10 minutes.
Grease large bowl.
Place dough in bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Work dough down and place in a greased loaf pan.
Let rise again to double the size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
While baking, rub bread with butter or margarine to make it nice and brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken and remove meat in bite-size chunks.
Chop celery, onion and pimento.
Add to chicken.
In small bowl, combine chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Fold into chicken and other ingredients.
Put mixture in a 1/2-quart buttered casserole and top with a ring of chow mein noodles, ring of toasted almonds and sprinkle center with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and bubbly.
Leftovers will reheat well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage; let stand 1 hour and squeeze out juice. Add carrot and pepper.
While cabbage is standing, make a syrup of vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage mixture; place in container and freeze.

title: easy chicken
directions: Rinse and dry dried beef.
Spread on bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on dried beef.
Cover with undiluted soup and sour cream, mixed.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove meat from bone and cut in small pieces.
Melt margarine in skillet and add celery, bell pepper and onion.
Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until done.
Add chicken and other ingredients.
Stir and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and pour over ingredients. Chill for 2 hours.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add garlic and saute. Add next 6 ingredients and 1/4 cup of water.
Heat to boiling. Stir.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir.

title: chewy chocolate and chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: rice stuffed flounder
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and mushrooms in hot margarine.
Mix broth, half and half, cornstarch and dill weed; add to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; return to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in carrot and zucchini.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stuff fish with mixture and sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake fish over any remaining mixture 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red hot crisp cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers in 1/2-inch slices.
Soak in lime in cold water, enough to cover cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours, stirring often.
Remove from lime water.
Wash in cold water; drain.
Add more cold water to cover.
Set 3 hours and drain.
Add vinegar and food coloring and cover with water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir often.
Drain liquid and discard.
Mix 5 1/2 pounds sugar, cinnamon sticks, red hots and 2 quarts vinegar.
Bring to boil and pour over cucumbers.
Set for 24 hours.
Drain juice and bring to boil.
Add to cucumbers again.
Do this for 3 days.
Then put all ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil and put in sterile jars and seal.
Put one cinnamon stick in each jar.
Makes 8 jars.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy (about 3 minutes).
Beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: beans and pork chop casserole
directions: Place beans in bottom of casserole.
Place the pork chops on top.
Mix the mustard, brown sugar, catsup and put on each pork chop.
Place a slice of onion and a slice of lemon on each pork chop.
Stick a toothpick in the center to hold in place.
Put in oven and cook for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
This is a delicious dish.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased 10 x 15 low sided pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Slice 5 to 6 apples into dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; spoon over apples.
Mix the flour, 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg together.
Beat egg; mix into flour mixture.
Spoon over apples evenly.
Melt the butter; drizzle over flour mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter with mixer on medium low.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Good served chilled and topped with whipped cream.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: touch of emerald
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water; set aside to cool.
Carefully and thoroughly blend cream cheese and half and half, then mix in the cooled jello.
Add pecans and pineapple; stir to mix only. Chill in refrigerator to set.

title: mexican egg rolls
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion together.
Fill the egg roll wrapper with hamburger, cheese and chilies. Roll and deep-fry until golden brown.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add salad oil, sugar, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350 F for 1 hour.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Put in oven and turn heat to 350° and bake about 1 hour.
Bake in 8-inch tube pan.

title: rhonda's butter chess pie
directions: Mix eggs with sugar and cornstarch until smooth.
Add melted butter, vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool and chill.
Similar to Furr's Butter Chess Pie.

title: canned vegetable casserole
directions: Drain corn (whole).
Combine creamed corn, cheese and soup. Fold in cauliflower, broccoli and whole corn.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and toss with crumbs. Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 370° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You can prepare ahead and chill.
If you do this, add 15 minutes more baking time.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Brown meat.
Cook onion until tender.
Stir in seasonings and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Mix in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan.
Place cherries in centers of pineapple rings.

title: creamed onions
directions: Make X's in root end of onions.
Cover with boiling water, let stand a few minutes (about 5).
Drain.
Cover with cold, salted water.
Bring to a rapid boil and cook until tender.
Drain.
Cut off ends.
Slip skins off (pinch at stem end).
Can be prepared up to 24 hours before using.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Bring onions to room temperature.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; arrange in casserole pan or dish.
Layer chicken (small pieces) on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top and then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dredge slices of salted tomatoes in corn meal. Fry in 1-inch of oil on medium/high heat until golden brown. Drain in single layers or paper towels.

title: linguine with clams and artichokes
directions: In stock pot, combine tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Do not boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms and simmer 10 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts and clams.
Heat.
Divide pasta into serving dishes and ladle sauce over pasta.
Sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley (optional).

title: quick and easy dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. When done, add milk and lay cheese on top
to melt.
Meanwhile, brown meat and onion together; drain grease.
Add meat and onion to macaroni and cheese.
Stir well to combine.
Add picante sauce (you may add more or less to your taste) and stir well.
Very good, easy and inexpensive.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with tamales, then put the browned ground beef on top of tamales.
Put Mexicorn on top of ground beef, then undiluted tomato soup and then crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and vanilla. Sift together remaining ingredients and fold into creamed mixture.

title: cranberry and apple casserole
directions: Mix cranberries and apples together in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle white sugar over the cranberries and apples.
Mix together oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Place on top of fruit and press down.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Especially good when served with turkey or chicken.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 10 minutes.
Cream soda, sugar, vanilla, eggs and shortening.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased bread pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and apples, let stand.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with apples.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for about 1 hour at 350°.
I use about 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon added, sprinkled on top.

title: deluxe carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt cake pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Check to see if done by inserting a toothpick in center.)

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add brown sugar and butter.
Cream well. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter in a medium bowl; mix until mixture is mealy. Combine sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook flour mixture over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Pour 1/2 cup of hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly. Add egg mixture to hot mixture, stirring constantly, until well combined. Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool. Add butter and vanilla to cooled mixture; set aside. Sprinkle half of peanut butter mixture on the bottom of a baked 9-inch pie shell. Top with custard. Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture over filling. Top with your favorite meringue. Bake at 200° until meringue is browned. Cool. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Grease large cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer, adding eggs in one at a time.
Pour 3/4 of the batter onto cookie sheet.
(Spread out, it is very thick.) Spoon on fruit.
Spoon on remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brazilian black bean salad
directions: In large bowl, stir oil, lime juice, cilantro, jalapeno, garlic, cumin and salt.
Add beans, onion and peppers.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain. Serves 6.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; boil for 10 to 12 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, make White Sauce.

title: hot spice tea mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
To serve mix 2 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Mix other ingredients.
Spread mixture on bread and roll up.
Dip in melted butter, then dip in cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: judy's brownies
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: karen's hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; save small amount of grated cheese for top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: greek pasta
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, cinnamon, nutmeg, tomato sauce and wine.
Cook on low 30 minutes.
Make a roux of 1/2 cup butter and flour.
Add hot milk and cook to thicken, making white sauce.
Add Ricotta cheese. Stir and keep warm.
Cook macaroni.
Add beaten eggs, 1/2 cup butter/margarine and half of the Cheddar cheese.
Add white sauce. Layer one-half of the macaroni mixture in bottom of large casserole.
The second layer is the meat mixture.
The third layer is the remaining macaroni mixture.
Top with the remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: puerto rican rum punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups pineapple juice in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; mix with remaining pineapple juice, lime juice and rum. Blend well. Place in freezer containers. Freeze until ready to serve. Yield: 20 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add the egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift together the flour and soda. Add flour alternately with sour cream. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Mop chicken each time turned.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan. Microwave chips and milk uncovered in microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth. Stir in sugar and vanilla, then walnuts (optional) until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Spread evenly.
Chill until firm (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cut into squares. Store in cool place.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and overlap on bottom of pizza pan to make crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes until brown.
Cool thoroughly. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread it over cookie crust.
Arrange sliced fruit over cream cheese.
Combine marmalade with water and spoon over fruit.
Chill in refrigerator. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex.
Freeze.

title: chicken casserole no. 4
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let chicken cool; remove bones and tear into small pieces.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed sparingly over topping.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together ground beef and taco seasoning.
In a large bowl mix all ingredients, except dressing and chips.
Refrigerate.
Add chips and dressing right before serving and toss again.
Recipe is party size.

title: cheesy grape salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve in lettuce cups.
This is especially good with meats.

title: lasagna
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste, basil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add cooking oil to large amount of boiling salted water; cook noodles 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse noodles.
Combine eggs, Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Layer half noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread half Ricotta mixture, half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together except margarine.
Dot top with margarine and bake for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well (before cooking).

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Bring to a boil the water, crushed pineapple and sugar.
Add jello and chill until partially set, then fold in the nuts and cream cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: portuguese soup(the inn at brushy creek)
directions: Saute onions and garlic in the oil.
When vegetables are transparent, add sausage slices and brown lightly.
Add beef stock and all other ingredients.
Bring soup to a boil, stirring to keep bottom of the pot from burning.
Reduce heat.
Allow to simmer 35 to 45 minutes or longer.

title: cheese dip
directions: Microwave Cheez Whiz briefly to soften.
Blend together Cheez Whiz
and Ranch dressing.
Good with crackers, any kind of chips or raw veggies.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all liquids.
Pour juices and ginger ale into punch boil.
Top with scoops of sherbet.
Serves 15.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Heat mustard and jelly together.
Mix in sliced meat.
Serve hot.

title: weight watcher's quiche
directions: Place onion, pepper, bacon bits and cheese in a 9-inch pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over vegetables in pan.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in soup, potatoes and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimentos, pepper and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into a shallow baking dish and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dried salty beef
directions: Slice the beef thin (do not cut off the fat).
In a large bowl, marinate the sliced beef with salt, nampla, pepper and m.s.g. for 2 hours.
In a saucepan, lay the sliced beef and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Fry the beef in deep oil until brown.
Remove from fat and drain.
Serve as side dish with curry or as hors d'oeuvres.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir ingredients together, adding blueberries last.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 435° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: lemon delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add lemonade.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat with mixer.
Add topping and beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar if you like.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small pieces.
Make a lot of gravy so you have enough to cover pieces.
Cook for 4 months.
This stew serves 4000 to 4006 people.
If more show up add 2 rabbits, but only if necessary.
Most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: fruit waffle and pancake syrup
directions: Drain fruit.
Add fruit juice to dry mixture; stir to dissolve.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes, or to medium thick syrup consistency.
Serve over pancakes and waffles.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°, 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together.
Cook over medium heat until mixture becomes a rolling boil.
Stir constantly for 15 minutes or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water, forms a soft ball. Remove from heat and add butter and peanut butter.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and egg.
Add all the dry ingredients.
Mix.
Chill in refrigerator and roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Mix first 5 ingredients and put in cooked shells.
Spray pan with Pam.
Mix soup with water and pour over top of filled shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt oleo, stir in peanut butter and powdered sugar and mix well.
Add graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Mix chocolate bits and paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and sit on rack to cool.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: elaine's zucchini lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef.
Drain fat.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper, carrots, tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spray a nonstick 8 x 12-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Remove ends of zucchini; slice lengthwise about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of baking dish.
Beat together cottage cheese and egg.
Spread over zucchini in baking dish.
Top with a layer of meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Layer remaining zucchini, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add soda.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss or begins to harden. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: pork chop scallop(stove top)
directions: In skillet, brown chops in margarine.
Remove chops and set aside.
Empty potatoes and packet of seasoned sauce mix into skillet.
Stir in water and milk called for on package.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and place chops on top.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and the chops are thoroughly done.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, lay chicken on top, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing evenly over all and drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Pull apart from bone in small pieces.
In a greased pan or oblong baking dish, crumble 1/2 box crackers.
Put cut-up chicken over crackers.
Mix both soups, chestnuts, sour cream and stock.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble 1/2 box of crackers over top and spoon melted margarine over the top. Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
This will make 2 small casseroles or 1 large one.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Put in sugar.
Add oil in slowly and beat well. Add vanilla and remaining dry ingredients. Add zucchini and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: aloha dip
directions: Cut one side off pineapple and make a boat; leave leaves on top.
Saw small place off on bottom of boat to flatten so it will set without rocking on a tray.
Mix sour cream, brown sugar and cookies.
Do not stir again; this is very important.
Place pineapple on tray; surround with pieces of fresh fruit (melons, strawberries, grapes bananas, etc.).
Add macaroon mixture into pineapple boat.
Serve toothpicks to dip fruit pieces into boat.

title: microwave spicy zucchini-tomato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except firm margarine in a large bowl. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with pieces of remaining butter.
Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes, rotating dish after 7 minutes of cooking.
When cooked, mixture will set into soft custard and zucchini will be slightly crunchy.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coffee bars
directions: Blend both sugars with shortening until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Separately sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beginning and ending with flour mixture, alternately mix with coffee into creamy mixture.
When blended, mix in vanilla and nuts.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops; place in casserole and top with vegetables, sauce and seasonings.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: meatball and vegetable stew
directions: Place meatballs and mixed veggies in 3 1/2 to 4 quart pot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems out of mushroom caps.
Fill with Rondelle cheese (found in dairy case with specialty cheeses).
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Add dot of butter to the foil around the mushroom caps.
Broil until the cheese is browned.
About 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil rice and cook 15 minutes.
Brown hamburger and drain. Add onion, tomatoes and corn.
Mix rice with all into greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: harlequin pinwheels
directions: Blend sugar and butter; beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Roll on lightly floured board to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: better 'n fried chicken
directions: Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken.
Put all ingredients in a plastic bag with chicken pieces and shake. Spray baking sheet with Pam.
Bake at 325° to 350° (according to oven) for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: spinach cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press all remaining liquid from spinach.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls; roll in additional Parmesan cheese if desired. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown and firm, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen appetizers.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Dredge fruits and nuts with 1 cup flour and spices. Fold into cake mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sugar coated chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Combine dry ingredients, except confectioners sugar, in large bowl.
Add chocolate mixture, eggs and vanilla, mixing until smooth.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Roll dough into 1-inch balls and roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and put in bowl, then layer bell pepper, onion, celery and peas.

title: frozen candy bars
directions: Mix the ingredients above thoroughly.
Line shallow 9 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Spread the mixture evenly.
Freeze.
To serve, cut into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yield:
36 bars.

title: blueberry-nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Drain blueberries; rinse and set aside.
Blend egg and milk.
Stir in muffin mix (dry) just until blended.
Batter should be lumpy. Fold in blueberries and nuts.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart casserole.
Combine ham, rice, peas, salt, mustard, pepper, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, Cheddar cheese soup and milk.
Turn into casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly.
If chilled before baking, bake 1 hour.

title: company cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of salted water in covered saucepan (about 4 minutes).
Drain.
Combine sour cream and dill seed.
Stir in cabbage and reheat.
Serves 4.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Put
peaches in Pyrex dish and pour mixture on top.
Bake at 375° until brown or about 45 minutes.

title: rice and ham stew
directions: Cut ham into small, bite size pieces and put in large pot. Add about 1/2 pot of water.
Add rice, chopped onion, sauce and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer until rice is done.
Add salt, pepper and a dash of Accent.

title: baked corn
directions: Put all ingredients into the beaten eggs.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, cutting off stems.
Saute onions and stems in butter.
Cook sausage and drain.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello and unflavored gelatin in hot water.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions with tops.
Mix all together with chopped beef.
Makes 2 balls.

title: creamy chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the chicken strips with mayonnaise or salad dressing. Add green onions, raisins and almonds; toss to coat. Mix until well blended. Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Place sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in saucepan.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes after mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir frequently. Remove from stove and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Place cupcake papers into muffin pans.
Fill papers as desired.
Let cool and eat.

title: doug's stir-up
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Heat corn until comes to a boil; cream potatoes according to package directions.
Put separate servings on a plate and stir up together, then enjoy.

title: coriander brown rice
directions: Place the rice and water in a heavy saucepan.
Add the salt, pepper, coriander and cardamom.
Cover and bring to a boil, stirring only once.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the butter and mix it in well.
The rice will stay hot with the lid on for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken corn casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and boil 1 minute.
Combine sauce, chicken and corn.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until browned on top.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Drain crab.
Reserve 1 piece crab for garnish.
Place all ingredients, except reserved crab and crackers, in bowl or food processor.
Process thoroughly.
Place in 2-cup serving dish. Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with reserved crab.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Place corn meal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in double boiler.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast softened in lukewarm water, then eggs. Beat thoroughly and let rise in warm place 2 hours.
Add flour to form soft dough. Knead well on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise until double and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken breast in casserole dish, 9 x 13-inches.
Cover with grated Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle with sherry or white wine. Mix cream of chicken soup with water and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle chips or dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with mayo.
Add sugar. Gently blend in cranberry sauce, oranges and walnuts. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in mold and freeze. Unmold. Slice to serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa until fluffy.
Add yolks and beat.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add to chocolate mixture and beat until thick enough to frost cake.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Mix sausage meat, oregano and egg together, add 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Mix well with hands, divide into three balls.
Using hands, wrap sausage meat around boiled egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (can be refrigerated up to 7 days).
Cool and cut into quarters, arrange on a lettuce-lined serving tray.
Great holiday appetizer. Usually the hit of the party!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and baking soda; blend.
Stir in shortening (oleo); add sour cream, corn and eggs.
Mix well.
Add green chilies and Cheddar cheese and stir.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar or margarine.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool.
Heat oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg at a time. Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake until center is firm, about 1 hour. Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours, but no longer than 10 days.
Loosen edge of cheese cake with knife before removing sides of pan.
Top with sour cream or glaze.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and de-bone chicken, reserving broth.
Chop chicken into small pieces and add 1/2 cup Picante sauce or to taste.
Set aside.
Into a Dutch oven, pour Pet milk and gradually add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Stir in the soup, sour cream, Ro-Tel tomatoes and 1 cup Picante sauce.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes to blend ingredients.
Dip tortillas into reserved hot chicken broth, one at a time just to soften.
On each tortilla, place equal amounts of chicken mixture; roll up and place into a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle any remaining chicken over the top.
Pour cheese sauce over the top of the chicken, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple bundt cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add flour mixture until well blended.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
