Bake at 375 for 1 hour. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Spread soup mixture on top.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box, using 1/2 broth and 1/2 water.
Spread on chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dough clay
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in heavy aluminum pan. Add water, oil, color and spice.
Heat on stove 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan.
Remove from heat and knead immediately.
Store in airtight container.
Clay keeps for several months.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Crush cornflakes into fine crumbs.
Blend shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, sugar, soda and butterscotch pieces.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll into cornflake crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and make indentation with thumb in center of each ball. Place 1/4 teaspoon peanut butter in each indentation.
Crumbs may also be sprinkled over peanut butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and bake for 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings, then add soup and water.
Into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish, alternate noodles and meat mixture.
Top with cheese slices and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until it bubbles.

title: strawberry rice salad
directions: Cook rice in water until tender (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain, reserving water.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup hot rice water.
Then combine gelatin, sugar, warm rice and pineapple.
When partially set, add whipped cream.

title: green frosting
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons water, stirring well.
Stir in desired amount of food coloring.
Add additional water for desired consistency, if necessary.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: gallets (waffle cookie)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour until dough is smooth but not dry. The amount of flour depends on the size of the eggs.
Heat waffle iron and measure a full tablespoon onto waffle iron for as many as it will make.
Start out with 4 and bake same as breakfast waffle until light brown.
This dough can also be refrigerated and rolled into balls, the size of walnuts.
Cookies are about 2 1/2-inches wide after baking.
If frosting is desired, any butter glaze will do.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch and butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs and sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Stir in butterscotch and pecans.
Cook in lightly greased pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Simmer all, except vegetables, until chicken is tender.
Then add vegetables.
Serve in bowl over tortilla chips and top with cheese.

title: round steak
directions: Bake at 350°.
Put layer of foil on baking sheet.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on foil.
Lay round steak on foil.
Sprinkle rest of onion soup on top.
Add mushrooms (drained) on top.
Cover with another piece of foil.
Seal tightly.
Bake 2 to 3 hours.

title: gravy
directions: Put hot water in pan; add salt.
Add flour to pan drippings. Stir.
Add to boiling water and stir.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and place in casserole dish.
Top with crackers and 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hat's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla together well. Sift flour.
Add flour, soda and salt to first mixture.
Fold in oatmeal, coconut, nuts and raisins.
Bake at about 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water. Drain and rinse in cold water. Drain well. Saute onion in butter until transparent, but do not brown. Add ground beef and cook until all the red color disappears, breaking with fork until crumbly. Combine meat with remaining ingredients and mix well with well drained macaroni. Pour into lightly oiled 2 1/2 qt. casserole dish. Sprinkle the top with additional cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes or until hot and light brown on top. Serves 6.

title: crawfish soup
directions: Combine tomato soup and crawfish tails.
Add enough water to suit your preferred consistency.
Blend mixture well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in shallow soup bowls and float croutons on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: layered finger jello
directions: 1st Layer:
Dissolve 1 package jello and 1 envelope gelatine in 1 cup boiling water and pour in 9 x 13 1/2-inch Pyrex baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Let set in refrigerator for 20 to 25 minutes until firm.
Dissolve 2 envelopes gelatine in 1 cup boiling water.
Add can of condensed milk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Layer in order given in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour dressing over top, but do not mix.
Let set in refrigerator at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, mix well.

title: orange sherbet molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and place in refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Mix in sherbet thoroughly.
Add drained oranges and pineapple.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mocha cake
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; blend well.
Stir in morsels and, if desired, brickle chips.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend well.
Add oregano, paprika or wine to your taste.

title: great pound cake
directions: In large bowl, put softened butter and cream cheese; blend together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; add sugar to this.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; slowly add these dry ingredients to the bowl.
Mix together well.
Add flavoring last.
Pour batter (very stiff) into 1 greased and floured tube pan or two loaf pans.
With knife, cut through cake batter in a circle.
Do not touch bottom of pan.
Place in center of rack and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Turn oven down to 325° and bake 1/2 hour more.
Cool and remove from pan.
Serve plain or add your favoring topping (optional).

title: potatoes scalloped with ham
directions: Layer 1/2 of ham, potatoes, onion, flour, salt and pepper. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Pour milk over layers.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle atop.
Top with parsley. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: mexican snack
directions: Combine cheese and green chilies; mix well.
Combine eggs and water and beat well.
Add to cheese mixture.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: In frying pan, brown beef in hot oil. Add garlic; cover and simmer until yellow. Add soy sauce and 1/4 c. water; cover and simmer 45 minutes. Add vegetables. Cook 10 minutes. Stir in cornstarch blended with rest of cup of water. Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into covered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with pickles and hot rolls.

title: energy bars
directions: Grease well a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine rice cereal, oats and sesame seed.
Toast over medium heat a few minutes.
In a large saucepan, combine marshmallows, peanut butter and butter; melt over low heat.
Stir in cereal mixture, peanuts and raisins.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Work fast.
Take out of pan and cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.
Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap.
Wax paper is easier to work with.

title: mom's stuffed shells
directions: Cook ground meat and onion in skillet until meat is cooked well, but not crisp.
Drain off fat.
Cook 1 pound jumbo shells until tender.
Set aside.
Mix meat, onion, sauerkraut and cooked potatoes together.
Fill cooked shells.
Sprinkle with dab of margarine.
Place in microwave for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good way to use up leftovers.

title: easy taco dip
directions: In a hurry?
This delicious dip can be put together with very little preparation.
Spread bean dip onto a big platter or shallow dish.
Spread guacamole next.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning and add the next layer.
Top with tomatoes and cheeses and sprinkle olives for garnish.
Serve with tortilla chips and extra salsa, if desired.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; peel.
Add butter and mash.
Cool.
Add milk and beat, adding salt and pepper to taste.

title: beef-cheddar macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef.
Drain fat and set aside.
In same skillet, saute onion in margarine.
In large bowl, combine beef, onion, spaghetti sauce, macaroni, mushrooms, 1 cup of the cheese and seasonings.
Spoon into a 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: frozen peaches
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Slice fresh peaches into freezer containers.
Pour mixture over peaches (as much as desired per container).
Fill not more than 3/4 full.
Crumple waxed paper and push peaches down to keep them from surfacing (as they will discolor).
Attach lid and freeze.
Thaw to serve.
Very good over ice cream or yogurt or whatever, using juices and all.

title: gooey chocolate cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together; cream until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until cookies are just set (tops will still be soft).
Remove from oven; let set a few moments before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 225° for 3 hours.

title: date and orange muffins
directions: Cut orange into pieces (do not peel).
Put in blender until rind is finely ground.
Add juice, dates, egg and butter.
Give a whirl in blender.

title: southern batter crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove bones and skin.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Place sliced boiled eggs over chicken.
Mix chicken broth and soup; heat and stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour broth over cut up chicken.
Pour flour mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter. Add sugar and crumbs and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco. Pour over peanut butter layer. Chill 20 minutes.
Score the chocolate.
Chill again 3 to 4 hours or until firm.

title: 7-layer cookie bars
directions: Place butter in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Place in warm oven to melt. Spread crumbs over butter.
Add one layer of remaining ingredients, dribbling milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: microwave strawberry jelly
directions: Mix strawberries and Sure-Jell in a 5-quart casserole dish. Stir and cover.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Take out.
Add 7 cups sugar. Stir well.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Stir well again and cook for 5 more minutes.
Take out and put in hot jars.
Seal.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saute the onions, green onions, bell pepper and celery in margarine until soft. Add flour, parsley and shrimp. Cook 15 minutes. Add relish, cheese and cream. Stir well until cheese is melted in sauce.
Mix with cooked fettucine and pour into casserole dish. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can substitute crawfish for shrimp.

title: m&m cookie mix
directions: Layer ingredients into jar in order given.
Press each layer firmly before adding the next ingredient.

title: veggie bars
directions: Roll out and press crescent rolls, seams together, on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: potato-clam soup
directions: Dice the potatoes and onions.
Volume-wise, make 1/2 volume of onions versus the potatoes.
Cook onions in oil until there are no crunchies, then add the remainder of the spices.
Simmer for 3 1/2 minutes.
Cover the potatoes with water; boil until semi-soft. Cook the bacon until it is thoroughly done, but not crisp.
Add the onion mixture to the potato pot.
This will seem like too much for the water.
It is, so now cut the temperature down so the water is not boiling.
Add the 2 cups of milk and clams; fold in the cream cheese.
The consistency should be about right.
If it is too loose, mix some flour and water in the mixer and add to suit your personal needs.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Mix with soup, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 cup cheese and half can of onions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining cheese and onions. Sprinkle over baked vegetables and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter and crumbs.
Spread half of crumbs in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Serves 6.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients (except corn) in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, over low heat, for approximately 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add corn last 5 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased round layer pan (9 x 1 1/2-inch or loaf pan).
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: coconut, pineapple cake
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar for 10 minutes.
When cake is done, poke holes in top and pour pineapple mixture over top.
Cook pudding and milk.
Spread over top of cake/pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut together and spread on top.

title: fancy rose's potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch (greased) pan.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange chicken and rice skillet
directions: Fry chicken in oil over medium heat until no longer pink.
Mix Miracle Whip, orange juice and brown sugar.
Add to chicken and simmer until chicken is done.
Add rice and green pepper strips and cook 3 minutes.
Add oranges and pineapple last and heat through.
Serve.
Makes 4 good servings.

title: holiday spiced tea
directions: Leave all ingredients in powdered form.
Put ingredients in a large bowl.
Put on a lid and shake well.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons of the powder per cup of hot water.

title: crispy chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Spread on 10 or 12 slices of bread and top with bread.
Wrap in freezer wrap and freeze.

title: special k squares
directions: Dissolve Karo syrup and brown sugar together in large pan. Do not boil.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in microwave or double boiler.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Cut in squares.

title: irish colcannon
directions: *Steam cabbage or cook in small amount of water and butter.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift the flour and salt together.
Cut in fat.
Add and stir in milk to make soft dough.
Divide dough in half.
Roll 1 part to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into strips.
Drop dumplings, 1 at a time, into liquid.
Keep dumplings pushed aside with fork so that dumplings will be separated.
Pour into baking dish.
Roll other half of dough to fit baking dish.
Place on top of chicken and crimp edges.
Slash crust to allow for escape of steam.
Brush crust with butter and bake.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese together.
Wash and core mushrooms. Put stuffing in mushrooms and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In mixer combine cooking oil, eggs and sugar.
Blend all wet ingredients, then put in all dry ingredients to mix well with apples.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process at high speed until smooth.
Serves with corn chips or tostados.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quick and easy fruit dip
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly with a fork.
Serve with fresh fruit or pound cake cut in pieces for dipping.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Combine Karo
and
sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately
and
add
peanut butter.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal.
Mix
well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; press flat. Melt
chocolate
morsels
and
spread evenly over all.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: jello ribbon salad
directions: Mix 1 box of Jello according to package directions.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Let set.
Mix second group of ingredients as a "filler".
Gently spread on top of set Jello.
Mix second box of Jello according to package directions.
Let it set until it starts to jell.
Spoon on top of filler and chill.

title: turkey tetrazzini(for leftover turkey!)
directions: Place turkey, water, bouillon cubes, onion, peas, mushrooms and cream soup in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.
In last hour, add spaghetti and cook until tender.
Serves 4.

title: rice wellington
directions: Mix rice, sugar, salt, soy sauce and boiling water; let stand. Brown meat, onions and celery; add soup and combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet until brown and crumbly. Drain. Stir in all tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Let simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes. Cook and drain noodles according to package. Stir together cooked noodles, green onions and sour cream until blended. Place noodle mixture in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with beef mixture and sprinkle evenly with cheese mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 5 to 8 minutes more.

title: bailey's chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick vegetable oil spray. Combine crumbs and sugar; stir in margarine. Press mixture into bottom and 1-inch up sides of pan. Bake until light brown, about 7 minutes. Maintain oven temperature at 325°.

title: shrimp dinner
directions: In heavy, deep skillet, saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and all seasonings.
Return to heat and simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes (add more water if needed).
Add clean, raw shrimp, bring to boil, reduce to medium and simmer 10-15 minutes, covered until shrimp are pink and tender.
Do not overcook.
Serve immediately over hot cooked rice.

title: sherlene green's cracker jacks
directions: Pop the popcorn and set aside.
Mix sugar, syrup and butter in saucepan and cook for 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour over popped corn; stir well and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes at 250°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate in cucumber dressing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients in one bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, then add 2 mixtures together.
Chill for 12 to 24 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions (drain fat).
Add tomato sauce, paste and tomatoes.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles for 10 - 12 minutes, drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine egg, ricotta or cottage cheese and parmesan cheese.
Layer 1/2 of the cooked noodles in a 2 qt rectangular baking dish.
Spread
1/2 of cheese mixture over noodles, then spread 1/2 of meat mixture over cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 30-35 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: spicey seasoned nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line jelly roll type pan (with sides) with foil.
Place nuts on foil.
Melt oleo and add seasonings, stirring well.
Pour mixture over nuts on foil and toss to coat. Bake 30 to 45 minutes till crisp.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: edible clay
directions: You will need waxed paper.

title: broccoli wreath
directions: In saucepan, bring one-inch water to a boil.
Add broccoli; cover and steam for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Plunge into ice water; drain.
Toss with salt and pepper.
Arrange florets and tomatoes in 12-cup ring mold.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
(Can be made ahead.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Bring to room temperature before baking.)
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. May use cheese sauce over this when serving.
Makes 20 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Stirring constantly, add water.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Dissolve.
Place berries in crust and pour hot mixture over berries.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift meal, flour, soda and sugar together.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 425° until done, approximately 20 minutes. You can use an iron skillet if you want to.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease 2-quart round casserole dish.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Using pastry blender, cut in butter.
Stir in raisins.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl beat eggs slightly with fork.
Remove 1 tablespoon of egg and reserve.
Stir in buttermilk in flour mixture (dough will be sticky).
Turn dough on well floured surface.
Knead dough 10 strokes to mix.
Shape in balls; place in casserole dish.
With sharp knife cut a 4-inch cross abut 1/2 inch deep in center of dough.
Brush with reserved egg.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in casserole on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from casserole dish.
Cool another 30 minutes, then cut and serve.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out the crescent roll dough onto a 9 x 13 inch baking sheet.
Pinch edges together to form the pizza crust.
Bake crust for 12 minutes in the preheated oven. Mix together in a small bowl, the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch-style dressing mix.
Spread this mixture over the cooled crust.
Arrange the vegetables over the cream cheese layer. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Chill for one hour, slice and serve.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to keep them stiff.
Cream shortening.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg yolks and beat until light and creamy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternating with the milk. Fold in beaten whites.
Fold in fresh blueberries.
(Take some flour called for in the receipt and shake them in it so they won't settle.)

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid, Jell-O and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water. Mix well and pour into plastic popsicle molds and freeze.

title: thailand peanut sauce
directions: 1. Blend or process the peanuts until they are fine meal. Reserve.

title: cherry in the snow pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy. Fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Pour pie filling over top. Chill and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine with apples.
Turn apple mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: hot butterscotch sauce
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and syrup until a teaspoonful will form a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and briskly stir in milk.
Keep hot in covered double boiler.

title: whole cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save and use 1 cup as liquid for Jell-O. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: egg rolls
directions: Stir-fry beef, chicken and onions in 1 tablespoon of oil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir-fry approximately 3 minutes.
Drain mixture and allow to cool.
Divide mixture and fill egg roll wrappers.
Deep fry in vegetable oil at 360° until crisp and brown.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix together sugar, egg, butter, milk and flour.
Cook until warm, then add vinegar.
Bring to boil, then cool.
Combine the cooled mixture with the bananas and crushed peanuts.
Place in serving bowl and scatter reserved peanuts over top.

title: crunchy fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 12 slices.
In a shallow bowl, whisk together flour, salt, sugar, and cayenne.
In another shallow bowl, whisk together egg and milk.
In a third shallow bowl, coarsely crush corn flakes with hands.
Working with one tomato slice at a time, dredge in flour, shaking off excess, and dip in egg, letting excess drip off.
Coat slices with corn flakes, pressing them to adhere, and arrange slices in one layer on a baking sheet.
In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat one tablespoon butter and one tablespoon oil over moderate heat until foam subsides.
Fry 3 tomato slices until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.
Be careful not to let coating burn.
Transfer tomatoes to paper towels and drain.
Fry remaining slices in remaining butter and oil in same manner.
On another baking sheet, arrange drained tomato slices in one layer.
Bake tomatoes in the middle of oven until tender and hot, about four minutes.
Serve with tomato salsa.

title: frango mint cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except Frango mints, in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in melted Frango mints.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan. After a few minutes, remove from pan.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick in blender for 15 seconds on high. Pour over hamburg.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with tomatoes.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesy apples
directions: Cut apples into wedges and put in baking dish.
Pour water and lemon juice over apples.
In another dish, mix remaining ingredients, including cheese.
Put on top of apples.
Cover and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and heat at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave. Serve with crackers.

title: oysters "to die for"
directions: Combine everything but parsley.
Pour in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The oysters will become tough if baked too long.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Cook rice.
In a casserole dish mix rice and broccoli together.
Add cheese mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Parsley and nuts are optional.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Soak yeast in milk, using 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat with a spoon.
Add sugar, shortening and salt. Beat.
Add other 1 1/2 cups flour.
Grease and let rise double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Put in greased 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Spread with sliced peaches or applesauce.
Sprinkle with topping:

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put
popcorn
in
large shallow roasting pan.
In heavy saucepan
mix
sugar,
butter, corn syrup and salt.
Stir over medium
heat until boiling.
Continue boiling without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn, stir to coat well.
Bake in preheated 250° oven 1
hour, stirring several times.
Cool, break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine the pudding mix and yellow cake mix in bowl.
Make well and pour in oil, milk and water.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon together.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Spread 1/2 of topping mixture. Add remaining batter and spread remaining topping mixture on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chunky rotel
directions: Cut cheese in chunks; melt in microwave and add Ro-Tel and ground beef.
Great with tortilla chips or sweet bread.

title: mushroom fried rice
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Brown rice and onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, soda and spices; add sugar and cream well.
Blend in molasses.
Beat in egg; add flour alternately with coffee (water).
Beat 1/2 minute; drop dough from teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix milk, sour cream, and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix with cake cubes.
Pour into a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Combine glaze and strawberries, and top the cake mixture.

title: meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water.
Add this to boiling water. Cook until clear. Let stand until completely cold.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add cornstarch mixture and beat on high speed, adding sugar gradually.
This makes a nice meringue.

title: goulash
directions: Brown pork steaks.
Then brown green peppers and onion.
In another bowl, bring to a boil beans and tomatoes.
Beat eggs and stir into beans and tomatoes.
Add to meat and vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brownie pie
directions: Combine and pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° until center quits jiggling (usually 20 minutes).
Bake longer for brownies.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut.
Press into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the cake mix as directed.
Pour over pecan and coconut mixture.
Mix the cream cheese, melted margarine and powdered sugar. Drop in rounded spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sister mary's noodle casserole
directions: Combine all together; put in baking dish and sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and pour melted 1/2 cup butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frances' ground beef casserole
directions: Cook 8 ounces elbow macaroni in salted water.
Drain and set aside.
Cook until lightly browned in skillet the beef, onion and pepper.
Add soup and milk.
Add drained macaroni.
Blend and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 or 20 minutes, until cheese is brown.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Add oil to large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour.
Brown quickly.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken.
Add onion slices, green pepper and garlic to skillet.
Cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove chicken from bones in large pieces.
Add chicken to sauce.
Cover tightly.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or spaghetti prepared according to package directions.

title: dale's plain cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add flour with buttermilk, alternately.
Put in large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: a gallon of fruit slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and turnip and place in a large container (12 quart for mixing purposes).
Add raisins, apples and drained pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix pineapple juice with Kraft dressing and pour over slaw.
Mix again so that the dressing is equally spread throughout.
Add additional dressing if more moistness is desired.
Store in a gallon jar or tightly closed container in the refrigerator to chill.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Melt
butter,
stir
in
sugar,
then add whipped eggs. Stir until smooth.
Add flour, stir, then add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Pour in Pam-sprayed 8-inch pie pan and microwave on High
for
to
minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: fried lumpia
directions: Saute garlic until brown, then discard.
In the same pan, saute onion until soft.
Add meat, shrimp and 1/2 cup cold water. Simmer for about 10 minutes or until pork is thoroughly cooked. Add beans, bean sprouts and carrots.
Cook for about 5 minutes more or just until tender.
If liquid remains, drain from mixture. Turn onto a large platter to cool.

title: baked beans with bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Mix pork and beans, catsup and sugar. Crumble bacon and add to mixture.
Keep out some bacon strips to cover the top.
Pour into medium casserole dish.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picnic cake icing
directions: Melt margarine, milk and cocoa together.
Bring to a boil. Stir in sugar, nuts and vanilla.

title: venison roast teriyaki
directions: You will also need 1 roast-in bag (if desired).

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in layers. Cool and ice.

title: potato cheese rivvel soup
directions: Cube potatoes; cook until almost done, covered in water.
Mix eggs, flour and salt until crumbly; drop into boiling potatoes. Cook until rivvels are tender.
Add the cheese; let melt, then add milk.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Turn heat to simmer; let cook about 20 minutes, or until gold and hot.
Be careful not to scorch cheese!

title: martha white candy
directions: Cream butter with hand.
Add sugar and vanilla, then add enough sweet milk to make soft balls.
Add coconut.
Make into little balls.
Cool in ice box.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on the package.
Combine 1 cup of the prepared whipped topping with the pie filling mix, pumpkin, milk and spices.
Mix slowly until just blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours.
Garnish with the remaining whipped topping.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook chopped cabbage in saltwater until tender. Saute onion in butter. Add cheese. Drain cabbage. Add soup and cheese mixture. Put 1/2 in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with half of crumbs. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs or Egg Beaters slightly with a fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients (except pie shell).
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven temperature down to 350°; bake another 30 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough onto large pizza pan.
Cook at 350 for 14 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto cookie.
Top with fruits.

title: low calorie chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix altogether until well blended.
Place in baking pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool.

title: melon smoothie
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender or food processor; process at high speed until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Stir all together with zucchini.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
This bread keeps well in freezer for months.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix altogether and drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve over crushed ice. Yields 2 1/2 gallons.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cover and soak beans in water overnight.
Pour out that water. Rinse and cover with cold water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil about 30 minutes.
Pour off water.
Rinse under hot water and put in casserole.
Mix together and add the remaining ingredients.
